name: Character EXP
desc: Character EXP, used to level up characters.

name: Adventure EXP
desc: Adventure EXP. Used to improve Adventure Rank.

name: Stardust
desc: Small talent points (Including the main character)

name: Starglitter
desc: Large talent points (Including the main character)

name: Companionship EXP
desc: Companionship EXP. Used to increase Friendship levels.

name: Original Resin
desc:
Used to vitalize Petrified Trees and Ley Line Blossoms, allowing access to the treasures they hold. Energy regenerates over time.
It is said that the roots of all the Irminsul trees and blossoms in the world are intertwined at the deepest, most hidden place in the earth, and that the pattern the root system makes defines the Ley Lines of the world.

name: Story Key
desc:
A key used to unlock Story Quests.
Obtained by completing the required number of Daily Commissions.

name: Fading Star's Might
desc:
A collection of celestial energy.
Can be exchanged for treasure during the "Unreconciled Stars" event.

name: Fading Star's Essence
desc:
Distilled celestial energy.
Can be exchanged for valuable treasure during the "Unreconciled Stars" event.
The essence of a faraway star. The power emanating from within is warm to the touch.

name: Glimmering Essence
desc:
A collection of vital energy that exudes a faint glimmer of light.
Can be exchanged for treasure during the event "The Chalk Prince and the Dragon."

name: Warm Essence
desc:
A collection of vital energy that exudes a gentle warmth.
Can be exchanged for precious treasure during the event "The Chalk Prince and the Dragon."

name: Miraculous Essence
desc:
A wondrous energy capable of reviving and mutating a withered Cryo Regisvine.
Can be exchanged for invaluable treasure during the event "The Chalk Prince and the Dragon."

name: Iron Coin
desc:
An ancient type of coinage that Ulman is collecting. Perhaps he may offer you something in exchange for Iron Coins.
Long ago, there was once an organization that attempted to found their own nation. These coins were the nation's minted currency at the time.

name: Peace Talisman
desc: Jade talismans that can be obtained during Lantern Rite. The people of Liyue believe that these talismans can bring and defend peace. You might be able to exchange these for some things during Lantern Rite...

name: Festive Fever
desc: The festive mood during Lantern Rite. Perhaps the atmosphere on the day of the Rite will be better the higher the Festive Fever is...

name: Veneficus Sigil
desc: A resource used to build all manner of mechanisms in the Theater Mechanicus. Still, the word "veneficus" itself seems to come from some old book...

name: Festive Tour Ticket
desc:
Take part in the celebratory activities of the Windblume Festival to obtain these tickets and exchange them in the event shop for rewards.
The people of Mondstadt are fun-loving by nature, and they have a celebration for the seasons, the harvests of different crops, and the anniversaries of events of historic significance. Perhaps there might be a festival to commemorate the outlander who repelled Stormterror someday...?

name: Peculiar Collab Coupon
desc:
Take part in the Windblume Festival event Domain to obtain these coupons and exchange them in the event shop for rewards.
This Domain of exceeding peculiarity is also part of the Windblume Festival celebrations, and it displays the fun-loving nature of Mondstadt's people.

name: Heart of the Spring
desc: The true heart of an Oceanid. This item is truly hard to find, for one must become one with the waters to truly perceive the heart of the springs.

name: Trust
desc: Accumulate this to increase your Trust Rank.

name: Fractured Fruit Data
desc: Irminsul Fruit fragment data that you have obtained via calculations and analysis performed by the Energy Amplifier. It contains a vast bounty of knowledge that may yet lead to surprising gains if you use it well.

name: Windtrace Coins
desc:
The currency that is awarded for participating in Windtrace.
The "background settings" of this same game will change in different areas. Though it is still a game of chase-and-catch, the fleeing party are named the "Rebels" in Mondstadt, while their pursuer is the "Hunter," symbols both of the ancient resistance and oppression.
Of course, the children of Mondstadt know well that this is just a game, and no true sense of enmity emerges as they play.

name: Shiny Flotsam
desc:
Shells brought in by the tide that shine gorgeously, filled with the breath of the sea.
Can be exchanged for precious treasures during the "Midsummer Island Adventure" event.

name: Mini "Harpastum"
desc:
These crystal-clear marbles have a bright feather sealed within them, making them miniature harpasta that are easy to collect.
Can be exchanged for precious treasures during the "Midsummer Island Adventure" event.

name: Enigma Gear
desc: Intricately crafted parts from Dodofortresses that look rather valuable. Can be exchanged for rewards.

name: Thunder Pellet
desc: A shard of concentrated violet lightning, fizzing with strange Electro energy. Can be exchanged for precious treasures during the "Thunder Sojourn" event.

name: Thunder Crystal
desc: A crystal formed from concentrated violet lightning, fizzing with strange Electro energy. Can be exchanged for valuable treasure during the event "Thunder Sojourn" event.

name: Mechanicus Mastery EXP
desc: Accumulate this to raise your Mastery Level. Raise your Mastery Level to obtain new Mechanici and Wondrous Sticks.

name: Wondrous Talisman
desc: A mysterious talisman obtained by playing Theater Mechanicus: Stage of Wonders. Exchange them with Komakata for some precious items.

name: Moonchase Festival Festive Fever
desc: Moonchase Festival Festive Fever

name: Battered Shikifuda
desc:
Shikifuda that have become terribly tattered. The intricate, esoteric charms have long ago become blurred and cannot be used in combat. However, the energy within these shikifuda is still sufficient to activate Charm Emplacements.
Use these items in the Labyrinth Warriors event to re-draw Charms.

name: Damaged Replica
desc:
Shikigami replicas whose charm magic has long since faded. They cannot reawaken Shiki Taishou's memories, but if gathered together, they can still help him reclaim his past power.
Use these items in the Labyrinth Warriors event to enhance Shiki Taishou's abilities.

name: Aged Token
desc:
Leftover wooden military ID tokens that record the names of the warriors who once fought within the Mystic Onmyou Chamber.
Exchange these items in the Labyrinth Warriors event for valuable treasure.

name: Snowstrider Seal
desc: An insignia given to those who complete the special training conducted by the Adventurers' Guild. It can be considered a symbol of one's strength.

name: Vanquisher's Emblem
desc: A precious insignia obtained from conquering a great trial. These emblems won't morph into anything else... Right?

name: Affluence Talisman
desc: A wondrous talisman said to be able to connect people to "fortune." In Liyue Harbor, many children are asked by their parents to carry this sort of talisman with them all the time.

name: Immaculate Talisman
desc: An exquisite talisman that seems quite valuable. You should be able to exchange this for certain items...

name: Conquest Talisman
desc: A strange talisman that appeared out of nowhere on your person. You can still feel powerful emotions emanating vaguely from this talisman when you hold it tight...

name: Moonlit Cragstone
desc:
A stone that gives off a strange radiance. It can only be found in a separate part of The Chasm, and its origins and composition are both unknown. However, it has strange and unique properties: When it falls, it maintains a regular shape and its cross-section still keeps its mirrored sheen. Those of these rocks that are older may have witnessed that ancient battle.
These stones can be exchanged for treasures during "Perilous Trail."

name: Iridescent Flotsam
desc:
The shell of some sea creature, hard in texture and scattered in the Golden Apple Archipelago. As if affected by a certain power, its surface loses all its natural patterns and becomes iridescent instead.
Can be exchanged for treasure during "Summertime Odyssey."

name: Stratagem Shard
desc:
A crystal that contains a deep and subtle power. Much like Cor Lapis, it has a pure Geo-gold hue. Its power can be activated to some extent within this space under The Chasm, thus helping to defeat monsters.
This can be used in the "Realms of Guile and War" of "Perilous Trails" to draw Stratagems or allow characters who have fallen to take to the field once again.

name: Creative Note
desc: After much discussion with your companions during the adventure, you summed up some thoughtful suggestions on how Aranara Carvings can become more popular. Can be exchanged for precious treasures during the "Graven Innocence" event.

name: Whimsical Draft
desc: A quick sketch of inspirations for "Aranara Carvings" made during the adventure. Can be exchanged for precious treasures during the "Graven Innocence" event.

name: Ancient Iron Coin
desc: Ancient iron currency which, according to Ulman, is worth an awful lot of money. However, it doesn't feel like anything special to the touch...

name: Festive Fever
desc: Weinlesefest Festive Fever

name: Business Earnings
desc: A sizable amount of Fairbrew Jelly, representing the sum total of your earnings in this charity event. As the Weinlesefest draws to a close, Bernhard will exchange these for Mora to give to old folks and children who need it.

name: Usable Funds
desc:
A sizable amount of Fairbrew Jelly, representing the base capital used in setting up your shop.
Attracting customers and increasing earnings — these two are the key goals of all shopkeepers. As such, you must plan out your spending and increase the attractiveness of your shop.

name: Strategic Inspiration
desc: Materials that contain various theories and case studies related to mercantile practice. To those with the appropriate experience, every page and every word is filled with possible inspiration for ways to improve.

name: Primogem
desc: A primordial crystalline gem that's beyond the mundane world. Shines with the condensed hopes and dreams of universes that once were.

name: Mora
desc: Common currency. The one language everybody speaks.

name: Genesis Crystal
desc: An energy crystal from the very origin of the universe. Formed from within nothingness out of pure potential and hope, it contains enough energy to create a newborn star.

name: Realm Currency
desc: Currency of the realm. Used within the Serenitea Pot to exchange for various items.

name: Original Essence (Invalidated)
desc: A crystal that temporarily revitalizes Irminsul to grant you ancient treasures. The energy within regenerates over time.

name: Original Resin (Invalidated)
desc: A crystal that temporarily revitalizes Irminsul to grant you great treasures. The energy within regenerates over time.

name: Masterless Starglitter
desc:
Currency used to purchase rare resources from the Shop.
Surplus Starglitter of destiny. Perhaps it can light up other corners of the universe.

name: Masterless Stardust
desc:
Currency used to purchase rare resources from the Shop.
Surplus Stardust of destiny. Perhaps it can create new destinies when in large enough quantities.

name: Intertwined Fate
desc:
A fateful stone that connects dreams.
Its glimmers can entwine fates and connect dreams, just as how its glimmers links stars into the shapes of a heart's desires.

name: Acquaint Fate
desc:
A seed that lights up the night.
No matter the distance apart, guided by the stone's glimmer, the fated will meet under the stars.

name: Pyro Sigil
desc: A token of recognition and appreciation that can be found around Mondstadt. Can be exchanged for rare items in the shop.

name: Hydro Sigil
desc: A token of recognition and appreciation that can be found around Mondstadt. Can be exchanged for rare items in the shop.

name: Dendro Sigil
desc:
A sigil that serves as a sign of recognition from the trees, grass, and flowers in Sumeru.
Offer it to the Tree of Dreams deep in the woods to receive the rewards from the forest.

name: Electro Sigil
desc:
A sigil that serves as a sign of the acknowledgment given by the thundering islands of Inazuma.
Offer them to the Sacred Sakura of the Grand Narukami Shrine to raise your Sacred Sakura's Favor level.

name: Anemo Sigil
desc:
An insignia that shows the recognition of the winds of Mondstadt.
Can be exchanged for special items in Mondstadt.

name: Cryo Sigil
desc: A token of recognition and appreciation that can be found around Mondstadt. Can be exchanged for rare items in the shop.

name: Geo Sigil
desc:
An insignia that shows the recognition of the cliffs of Liyue.
Can be exchanged for special items in Liyue.

name: Mondstadt Reputation EXP
desc: Increases your Reputation Lv. (Mondstadt)

name: Liyue Reputation EXP
desc: Increases your Reputation Lv. (Liyue)

name: Inazuma Reputation EXP
desc: Increases your Reputation Lv. (Inazuma)

name: Sumeru Reputation EXP
desc: Increases your Reputation Lv. (Sumeru)

name: Memory of Eternal Flames
desc: The missing star from the Talents of a Pyro-aligned Traveler.

name: Memory of Running Stream
desc: The missing star from the Talents of a Hydro-aligned Traveler.

name: Memory of Flourishing Green
desc: The missing star from the Talents of a Dendro-aligned Traveler.

name: Memory of Violet Flash
desc: The missing star from the Talents of an Electro-aligned Traveler.

name: Memory of Roving Gales
desc: The missing star from the Talents of an Anemo-aligned Traveler.

name: Memory of Piercing Frost
desc: The missing star from the Talents of a Cryo-aligned Traveler.

name: Memory of Immovable Crystals
desc: The missing star from the Talents of a Geo-aligned Traveler.

name: Kamisato Ayaka
desc: Daughter of the Yashiro Commission's Kamisato Clan. Dignified and elegant, as well as wise and strong.

name: Jean
desc: The righteous and rigorous Dandelion Knight, and Acting Grand Master of Mondstadt's Knights of Favonius.

name: Male Character
desc: A traveler from another world who had their only kin taken away, forcing them to embark on a journey to find The Seven.

name: Lisa
desc: The languid but knowledgeable Librarian of the Knights of Favonius, deemed by Sumeru Akademiya to be their most distinguished graduate in the past two centuries.

name: Female Lead
desc: A traveler from another world who had their only kin taken away, forcing them to embark on a journey to find The Seven.

name: Barbara
desc: Every citizen of Mondstadt adores Barbara. She learned the word "idol" from a magazine.

name: Kaeya
desc: An accomplished swordsman and a strategic thinker in the Knights of Favonius, rumored to hail from beyond Mondstadt.

name: Diluc
desc: The tycoon of a winery empire in Mondstadt, unmatched in every possible way.

name: Razor
desc: A boy who lives among the wolves in Wolvendom of Mondstadt, away from human civilization. As agile as lightning.

name: Amber
desc: Always energetic and full of life, Amber's the best — albeit only — Outrider of the Knights of Favonius.

name: Venti
desc: One of the many bards of Mondstadt, who freely wanders the city's streets and alleys.

name: Xiangling
desc: A renowned chef from Liyue. She's extremely passionate about cooking and excels at making her signature hot and spicy dishes.

name: Beidou
desc: Captain of her crew, The Crux. She's quite an unbound and forthright woman.

name: Xingqiu
desc: A young man carrying a longsword who is frequently seen at book booths. He has a chivalrous heart and yearns for justice and fairness for all.

name: Xiao
desc: A yaksha adeptus who defends Liyue. Also heralded as the "Conqueror of Demons" and "Vigilant Yaksha."

name: Ningguang
desc: The Tianquan of the Liyue Qixing. Her wealth is unsurpassed in all of Teyvat.

name: Klee
desc: An explosives expert and a regular at the Knights of Favonius' confinement room. Also known as Fleeing Sunlight.

name: Zhongli
desc: A mysterious expert contracted by the Wangsheng Funeral Parlor. Extremely knowledgeable in all things.

name: Fischl
desc: A mysterious girl who calls herself "Prinzessin der Verurteilung" and travels with a night raven named Oz.

name: Bennett
desc: A good-natured adventurer from Mondstadt who's unfortunately extremely unlucky.

name: Tartaglia
desc: No. 11 of The Harbingers, also known as "Childe." His name is highly feared on the battlefield.

name: Noelle
desc: A maid who faithfully serves the Knights of Favonius. She dreams of joining their ranks someday.

name: Qiqi
desc: An apprentice and herb gatherer at Bubu Pharmacy. An undead with a bone-white complexion, she seldom has much in the way of words or emotion.

name: Chongyun
desc: A young exorcist from a family of exorcists. He does everything he can to suppress his abundance of yang energy.

name: Ganyu
desc: The secretary at Yuehai Pavilion. The blood of the qilin, an illuminated beast, flows within her veins.

name: Albedo
desc: A genius known as the Kreideprinz, he is the Chief Alchemist and Captain of the Investigation Team of the Knights of Favonius.

name: Diona
desc: A young lady who has inherited trace amounts of non-human blood. She is the incredibly popular bartender of the Cat's Tail tavern.

name: Mona
desc: A mysterious young astrologer who proclaims herself to be "Astrologist Mona Megistus," and who possesses abilities to match the title. Erudite, but prideful.

name: Keqing
desc: The Yuheng of the Liyue Qixing. Keqing has much to say about Rex Lapis' unilateral approach to policymaking in Liyue — but in truth, gods admire skeptics such as her quite a lot.

name: Sucrose
desc: An alchemist filled with curiosity about all things. She researches bio-alchemy.

name: Xinyan
desc: Liyue's sole rock 'n' roll musician. She rebels against ossified prejudices using her music and passionate singing.

name: Rosaria
desc: A sister of the church, though you wouldn't know it if it weren't for her attire. Known for her sharp, cold words and manner, she often works alone.

name: Hu Tao
desc: The 77th Director of the Wangsheng Funeral Parlor. She took over the business at a rather young age.

name: Kaedehara Kazuha
desc: A wandering samurai from Inazuma who is currently with Liyue's Crux Fleet. A gentle and carefree soul whose heart hides a great many burdens from the past.

name: Yanfei
desc: A well-known legal adviser active in Liyue Harbor. A brilliant young lady in whose veins runs the blood of an illuminated beast.

name: Yoimiya
desc: Owner of Naganohara Fireworks. Known as the "Queen of the Summer Festival," she excels in her craft of creating fireworks that symbolize people's hopes and dreams.

name: Thoma
desc: The Kamisato Clan's housekeeper. A well-known "fixer" in Inazuma.

name: Eula
desc: The Spindrift Knight, a scion of the old aristocracy, and the Captain of the Knights of Favonius Reconnaissance Company. The reason for which a descendant of the ancient nobles might join the Knights remains a great mystery in Mondstadt to this very day.

name: Raiden Shogun
desc: Her Excellency, the Almighty Narukami Ogosho, who promised the people of Inazuma an unchanging Eternity.

name: Sayu
desc: A pint-sized ninja attached to the Shuumatsuban, who always seems sleep-deprived.

name: Sangonomiya Kokomi
desc: The Divine Priestess of Watatsumi Island. All of the island's affairs are at this young lady's fingertips.

name: Gorou
desc: The great general of Watatsumi Island's forces. He is deeply trusted by his subordinates.

name: Kujou Sara
desc: A general of the Tenryou Commission. Bold, decisive, and skilled in battle.

name: Arataki Itto
desc: The first and greatest head of the Arataki Gang, famed throughout Inazuma City's Hanamizaka... Wait, what? You've never heard of them? Are you trying to be funny here?

name: Yae Miko
desc: Lady Guuji of the Grand Narukami Shrine. Also serves as the editor-in-chief of Yae Publishing House. Unimaginable intelligence and cunning are hidden under her beautiful appearance.

name: Shikanoin Heizou
desc: A young prodigy detective from the Tenryou Commission. His senses are sharp and his thoughts are clear.

name: Yelan
desc: A mysterious person who claims to work for the Ministry of Civil Affairs, but is a "non-entity" on the Ministry of Civil Affairs' list.

name: Aloy
desc: Formerly an outcast, now a hunter of unparalleled skill. Ready to do the right thing at any time.

name: Shenhe
desc: An adepti disciple with a most unusual air about her. Having spent much time cultivating in isolation in Liyue's mountains, she has become every bit as cool and distant as the adepti themselves.

name: Yun Jin
desc: A renowned Liyue opera singer who is skilled in both playwriting and singing. Her style is one-of-a-kind, exquisite and delicate, much like the person herself.

name: Kuki Shinobu
desc: The capable and reliable deputy leader of the "Arataki Gang" - Please note: capable and reliable are not appellations for the "Arataki Gang," but for their deputy leader in specific.

name: Kamisato Ayato
desc: The young but highly accomplished head of the Yashiro Commission's Kamisato Clan. Cultured and polite, he is a man of many ways and means.

name: Collei
desc: A trainee ranger active in Avidya Forest. Behind her enthusiastic words and actions hides a slightly introverted personality.

name: Dori
desc: An elusive merchant who has a fondness for glittering Mora.

name: Tighnari
desc: A young researcher well-versed in botany who currently serves as a Forest Watcher in Avidya Forest. He is a straight shooter with a warm heart — and a dab hand at guiding even the dullest of pupils.

name: Nilou
desc: The star of the Zubayr Theater. She is full of warmth and innocence, and her dances are lively and elegant.

name: Cyno
desc: The General Mahamatra in charge of supervising the researchers of the Akademiya. It is said that when he gets down to work, the General Mahamatra is even more efficient than the "Great Vayuvyastra" made by the Kshahrewar.

name: Candace
desc: A descendant of King Deshret with an amber left eye. The defender of Aaru Village.

name: Gnostic Hymn - Old Notes
desc:
An early draft of a traveler's tale, recording the many things they saw on their journey across the lands. But why does it exist? It is almost as if you have been here before...

Use this item to unlock Gnostic Hymn for a single period.

name: Blessing of the Welkin Moon - New Moon
desc:
A ritual prayer, recited on the rising of the first new moon, to ask for the moon's blessing in the form of wealth and good fortune. For your purposes, the new moon you shall pray to is the first-ever new moon in Teyvat, since it's the first one you've seen here.

Use this item to receive 30 days of Blessing of the Welkin Moon rewards.

name: Kaeya
desc: An accomplished swordsman and a strategic thinker in the Knights of Favonius, rumored to hail from beyond Mondstadt.

name: Lisa
desc: The languid but knowledgeable Librarian of the Knights of Favonius, deemed by Sumeru Akademiya to be their most distinguished graduate in the past two centuries.

name: Apple
desc: Crisp and fragrant. Delicious raw or made into wine.

name: Sunsettia
desc: A plump fruit, beautiful like the sunset, that is abundant across all of Teyvat. It has a curious, sweet aroma and is able to energize an individual.

name: Mushroom
desc: Hardy common fungi. Can grow anywhere with the right amount of shade and moisture.

name: Sweet Flower
desc: Particularly fragrant flowers. They can be found easily, even in the dark. Just follow the scent.

name: Carrot
desc: A healthy and nutritious vegetable that is crunchy and sweet to the taste. Easy to grow and harvest.

name: Radish
desc: Rich in fiber and nutrients. Easy to grow and harvest.

name: Snapdragon
desc: Can be eaten once cooked. As a spice, it can bring wonderful flavor to dishes.

name: Mint
desc: A refreshingly cool ingredient. The cool, fresh flavor can cut through the heat of many dishes.

name: Wheat
desc: Golden, sun-kissed tassels. Needs to be ground down to flour for further use.

name: Cabbage
desc: A layered, leafy vegetable. Said to have originally been an ornamental plant, it certainly looks great in the pot.

name: Silver Lotus
desc: A rare plant that grows on steep cliffs with nobility. Shines magnificently in the night.

name: Pinecone
desc: Filled with oil-rich seeds. Certainly won't be growing into a tree from inside a squirrel's stomach.

name: Wolfhook
desc: A berry with thorns that often gets attached to a wolf's pelt. When you look at it, you can almost hear the echoing cries of the wolves in the woods.

name: Valberry
desc: A plump and translucent berry that has a fragrant smell and a sweet, refreshing taste. In the past, the storm watchers' only solace was the sweetness of this fruit and hope for the city's peace.

name: Cecilia
desc: A beautiful flower with a name that suits its appearance. It only grows where harsh winds blow, and is just as intangible as the true heart of an unbound soul.

name: Windwheel Aster
desc: A plant that adores the wind. To the proud children of the wind, or the citizens of Mondstadt, the Windwheel Asters are "the visible winds."

name: Philanemo Mushroom
desc: A fungus that grows in the warm caress of the wind. It is as everlasting as the wind, nourishing life.

name: Lotus Head
desc: An aquatic plant native to Liyue that grows and blooms in pairs. One is fragrant, and the other bitter. It's said to make a good herbal medicine.

name: Jueyun Chili
desc: A spicy plant native to Liyue. Merely smelling it makes one hot and thirsty.

name: Noctilucous Jade
desc: A rare mineral that glimmers in the dark. It's said to be a mutated gemstone condensed from the flourishing elements of the world.

name: Silk Flower
desc: A crimson flower that blooms like the rainbow clouds in Liyue. It can be made into silky-smooth fabric.

name: Glaze Lily
desc: An extremely ancient flower that was said to be commonly seen in Liyue. It transforms the memories of the land into its fragrance during florescence.

name: Qingxin
desc: A translucent white flower that only grows on the highest stone peaks. It eschews the warmth and moisture of the plains to gaze out afar from the solitary mountaintops.

name: Horsetail
desc: A purple plant that sometimes grows amidst Silvergrass but grows taller, straighter, and plumper — like an aristocrat among the paupers.

name: Starconch
desc: Empty seashells brought ashore by the tides. Hold it close to your ear, and hear the longing calls of the sea.

name: Violetgrass
desc: A small flower with strong vitality. It is said that its downward-blooming flower keeps its fragrance from dissipating.

name: Berry
desc: Small, brightly-colored fruit. They can be found everywhere, and the taste of them wipes the fatigue of a long journey away.

name: Mist Flower Corolla
desc: A flower bud encased in solid ice. Even after being picked, the flower continues to emit cold.

name: Flaming Flower Stamen
desc: The stamen of a fiercely burning flower. Even after being extinguished, it still emits heat.

name: Electro Crystal
desc: A power-rich crystal that draws electricity from the air around it. Holding it makes your hand a little numb.

name: Small Lamp Grass
desc: A wild grass that emits light at night. Used in cooking to enhance other flavors.

name: Calla Lily
desc: A flower that grows near water sources. When cooked, the petals have a chunky texture, yet are sweet and a little bitter.

name: Dandelion Seed
desc: A tiny seed that rides on the wind. Even without its feathered wings, it still holds the hope from afar within.

name: Cor Lapis
desc: A precious crystal of condensed pure Geo element that usually grows along with other minerals. It's also commonly called "Cor Petrae."

name: Raw Meat
desc: A fresh chunk of meat. Handled properly, it can be used to make delicious food.

name: Bird Egg
desc: An incredibly versatile ingredient that can supply all of your daily protein needs.

name: Matsutake
desc: A rare fungus that generally grows on or near pine trees. Its delicate aroma gives away its location.

name: Fowl
desc: A fresh chunk of fowl. Handled properly, it can make a hearty meal.

name: Butterfly Wings
desc: Brightly colored wings. The powder that falls from them shimmers a little. Perhaps this is what allows them to fly?

name: Crab
desc: A shelled creature that lives near the ocean. Its flaky, delicious meat can easily be made into tasty dishes.

name: Crab Roe
desc: A delicacy specific to female crabs. A rare and prized ingredient that isn't quite to everyone's taste.

name: Salt
desc: A savory seasoning. A precise but adequate amount will elevate the quality of the cuisine.

name: Onion
desc: A spherical vegetable. As vengeance for cutting it, it will make you cry, no matter how brave you are.

name: Pepper
desc: Peppery. Cuts through oily flavors and excites the taste buds. Goes best on meat.

name: Milk
desc: Sweet and fragrant cow's milk. Don't waste a single drop, not even that one rolling down your chin.

name: Tomato
desc: A bright red ingredient that gives a tangy kick. Yes, the "fruit or vegetable" debate is still going...

name: Potato
desc: A chunky vegetable. A gift from the earth that you never tire of with its multitude of cooking methods.

name: Frog
desc: Common frog found in moist environments. Full of energy, they secrete a substance that will keep you full of vitality.

name: Luminescent Spine
desc: The light-emitting part of a firefly. Used for courtship, and in medicine to help recover strength.

name: Lizard Tail
desc: A lizard tail that curled up after losing its owner. Very bitter, but has skin hardening properties.

name: Fish
desc: A fresh fillet of fish. Handled properly, it can make a rich dish.

name: Crystal Core
desc: The core of a crystal butterfly. It absorbs elemental energy that has escaped into the atmosphere.

name: Raw Meat (S)
desc: A fresh chunk of meat. Handled properly, it can be used to make delicious food.

name: Fowl (S)
desc: A fresh chunk of fowl. Handled properly, it can make a hearty meal.

name: Tofu
desc: Freshly made bean product that has a silky-smooth tender texture.

name: Almond
desc: A seed with a peculiar fragrance that gives food a refreshing taste.

name: Loach Pearl
desc:
A shiny pearl spat out by a loach that has mystical medicinal properties.
Minerals and elemental particles ingested by the loach condense into these mildly magical beads. When threatened, the loach spits them out to confuse predators and escape with its life.

name: Bamboo Shoot
desc: A fresh young bamboo shoot, straight out of the ground. It is a delicious cooking ingredient with an exotic aroma, found exclusively in bamboo-growing regions.

name: Rice
desc: A grain crop commonly found in Teyvat. People of all walks of life enjoy its distinct grainy texture. As the saying goes, "The same kind of rice can feed one hundred kinds of people."

name: Shrimp Meat
desc: A whole piece of deep sea shrimp meat, full of nutrients and bursting with delicious flavor.

name: Chilled Meat
desc:
Rare, fresh meat.
This species of boar is recorded to have gone extinct several hundred years ago and has been preserved by the extreme temperatures on Dragonspine. For the gourmets of Teyvat, this is an ingredient of unspeakable sacrosanctness.

name: Unagi Meat
desc: The fresh meat of an Unagi. If handled properly, it can be used to make fresh, lovely food.

name: Glabrous Beans
desc: A common legume in Teyvat with a light aroma. It can be prepared in a variety of ways, and is thus widely accepted by people all over the world.

name: Iron Chunk
desc: This iron chunk can be turned into a multitude of handy items in the hands of a skilled craftsman.

name: White Iron Chunk
desc: Skilled hands can make this into something brilliant.

name: Crystal Chunk
desc: An uncut crystal. Only professional craftsmanship can bring out its true value.

name: Magical Crystal Chunk
desc:
These crystal chunks can be refined into Weapon EXP materials by using Original Resin.
Crystals from mines that were eroded by the energy of the Ley Lines cannot be processed by ordinary means.

name: Scarlet Quartz
desc: Scarlet Quartz

name: Starsilver
desc: A rare and precious ore formed by the unique geographical conditions and Ley Lines of Dragonspine.

name: Scarlet Quartz
desc: Scarlet Quartz (Dragonspine Event)

name: Amethyst Lump
desc: An uncut crystal that can only be found in Inazuma. Some professional craftsmanship will bring out its true value.

name: Northlander Sword Billet
desc:
Weapon forging material. Can be used to forge 4-star swords. 
Philosophers believe marble has the potential to be sculpted into a beautiful statue. Likewise, these billets have the potential to become something greater.

name: Northlander Bow Billet
desc:
Weapon forging material. Can be used to forge 4-star bows. 
Philosophers believe marble has the potential to be sculpted into a beautiful statue. Likewise, these billets have the potential to become something greater.

name: Northlander Claymore Billet
desc:
Weapon forging material. Can be used to forge 4-star claymores. 
Philosophers believe marble has the potential to be sculpted into a beautiful statue. Likewise, these billets have the potential to become something greater.

name: Northlander Catalyst Billet
desc:
Weapon forging material. Can be used to forge 4-star catalysts. 
Philosophers believe marble has the potential to be sculpted into a beautiful statue. Likewise, these billets have the potential to become something greater.

name: Northlander Polearm Billet
desc:
Weapon forging material. Can be used to forge 4-star polearms. 
Philosophers believe marble has the potential to be sculpted into a beautiful statue. Likewise, these billets have the potential to become something greater.

name: Northlander Sword
desc: An unknown sword from the Northlands

name: Northlander Bow
desc: An unknown bow from the Northlands

name: Northlander Claymore
desc: An unknown claymore from the Northlands

name: Northlander Catalyst
desc: An unknown catalyst from the Northlands

name: Northlander Polearm
desc: Unknown Northlander Polearm

name: Midlander Sword Billet
desc:
Weapon forging material. Can be used to forge 4-star swords.
Philosophers believe that there are four purposes behind earthly things. The purpose of these billets is to become a weapon worthy of accompanying a hero.

name: Midlander Bow Billet
desc:
Weapon forging material. Can be used to forge 4-star bows.
Philosophers believe that there are four purposes behind earthly things. The purpose of these billets is to become a weapon worthy of accompanying a hero.

name: Midlander Claymore Billet
desc:
Weapon forging material. Can be used to forge 4-star claymores.
Philosophers believe that there are four purposes behind earthly things. The purpose of these billets is to become a weapon worthy of accompanying a hero.

name: Midlander Catalyst Billet
desc:
Weapon forging material. Can be used to forge 4-star catalysts.
Philosophers believe that there are four purposes behind earthly things. The purpose of these billets is to become a weapon worthy of accompanying a hero.

name: Midlander Polearm Billet
desc:
Weapon forging material. Can be used to forge 4-star polearms.
Philosophers believe that there are four purposes behind earthly things. The purpose of these billets is to become a weapon worthy of accompanying a hero.

name: Onikabuto
desc: A strange beetle that inhabits areas rich with Electro energy. Its docile and sedentary temperament could not be more different from the fierce, demonic visage displayed on its armored shell.

name: Sakura Bloom
desc: Blossoms from the Sacred Sakura at the Grand Narukami Shrine, filled with a fondness for Inazuma.

name: Crystal Marrow
desc: A crystal that contains a sliver of Tatarigami power. Adding this material during smelting will greatly increase the strength and toughness of metals.

name: Dendrobium
desc: A vibrant plant that has also been named the "lycoris" by the poets. It was once thought extinct in the Inazuman archipelago, only to re-emerge now upon the battlefields. It is said that it blooms most enchantingly where much blood was spilled.

name: Naku Weed
desc: Even on windless days, this plant will tremble lightly amid the cries of thunder. The parts of it that resemble petals are in fact extensions of the leaves meant to protect the fragile flower.

name: Sea Ganoderma
desc: A plant species that only grows in certain regions and islands of the ocean. Though it looks like a fungus of some sort, it actually comes from a substance secreted by certain soft-bodied organisms.

name: Sango Pearl
desc: A precious pearl that grows in the coral of Watatsumi. Gives off a cool sheen like that of the moonlight.

name: Amakumo Fruit
desc: The fruit of the Amakumo Grass, which grows on Seirai Island. You can hear it crackling with a tiny current if you hold it up to your ear.

name: Fluorescent Fungus
desc: A mushroom that glows like a night-light. Some curious power lies hidden within it.

name: Seagrass
desc: A plant that grows in shallow seas. It adds a unique flavor to dishes.

name: Lavender Melon
desc: A brightly-colored fruit. The flesh within transforms into food with a unique mouthfeel when cooked.

name: Starshroom
desc: A fungus with a cap that resembles a five-pointed star. It is quite hardy indeed. Once it matures, the center of the cap will split open.

name: Rukkhashava Mushrooms
desc: A fungus that grows in layers upon layers, like a sea of clouds, and which mostly grows on trees deep in the rainforest. Therefore, they are considered by the people of Sumeru to be the holy crystallization of Rukkhadevata's legacy.

name: Padisarah
desc: A holy and noble plant. The conditions for growth in its environment are very demanding. The flower buds can be processed to make valuable spices.

name: Nilotpala Lotus
desc: Growing in the forest wetlands, these plants only bloom at night with flowers as bright as the moon.

name: Harra Fruit
desc: Growing in the hot humid rainforest, it is a fruit with a special spicy aroma. When ground to powder, spices can be made from it. It is the most valued spice plant in Sumeru.

name: Kalpalata Lotus
desc: Flowers from vines that grow on cliff sides. It is called a lotus only because it has a similar appearance to one. Aside from that, it bears no other similar properties to the lotus.

name: Zaytun Peach
desc: The fruit of a forest shrub. Its flesh is firm and sweet. It is said to have a calming effect on the mind.

name: Sumeru Rose
desc: Bright and beautiful, these pure purple flowers give off a pleasant fragrance that will give any passerby pause. While some like to call this a type of "rambler rose," its relative lack of multiple flowers means that it falls under a different floral classification.

name: Redcrest
desc: A fruit that grows even in the most hostile of desert environments. Its vibrant crimson fruits are made even more lovely against a backdrop of yellow sand.

name: Ajilenakh Nut
desc: A fruit that grows on evergreen trees within desert oases. The flesh under the tough skin is thick, sweet, and delicious, making it an important food source amongst the desert peoples.

name: Scarab
desc: A tenacious beetle that finds repose within the vast ocean of desert sand. The golden pattern on such beetles' shells hints at some deep relationship between them and the ancient ruins that dot the desert.

name: Activated Starshroom
desc: A fungus with a cap that resembles a five-pointed star. It seems to be bursting with vitality.

name: Scorched Starshroom
desc: A fungus with a cap that resembles a five-pointed star. It seems to be a little singed.

name: Viparyas
desc:
A flower without seeds. 
Once the earth remembers, the Viparyas will bloom.

name: Birch Wood
desc:
Timber obtained from birches. It is easy to work with and produces smooth cuts. Furniture made using such wood is both beautiful and durable.
Can be used to create furnishings.

name: Cuihua Wood
desc:
Timber obtained from Cuihua Trees. With its lovely color and unique make, it will surely be able to take on myriad uses upon undergoing suitable workmanship.
Can be used to create furnishings.

name: Pine Wood
desc:
Timber obtained from pines. Its color and grain are nothing to write home about, but its unpretentious nature is elegant in its own right. The wood is very sturdy as well. In able hands, its products should be able to resist moth and rot alike.
Can be used to create furnishings.

name: Sandbearer Wood
desc:
Timber from the Sandbearer Tree. Said to be an exceptionally hardy plant resistant to wind and rain with a long lifespan.
Can be used to create furnishings.

name: Bamboo Segment
desc:
Segments of bamboo that are light and far stronger than their humble appearance might suggest. It lets off a light fragrance.
Can be used to create furnishings.

name: Fragrant Cedar Wood
desc:
Wood from the Cedar tree. Also known as the "Fragrant Cedar" for the aromatic oils it contains.
Can be used to create furnishings.

name: Fir Wood
desc:
Wood from the tree known as "Faber's Fir." Widely used for its fine quality and attractive grain.
Can be used to create furnishings.

name: Yumemiru Wood
desc:
Timber obtained from Sakura Trees. Exquisite in quality and full of moisture, people say that it can lull people into dreams as sweet as the warm spring.
Can be used to create furnishings.

name: Maple Wood
desc:
Timber from the Amur Maple. Excellent quality wood with a fine color and texture.
Can be used to create furnishings.

name: Aralia Wood
desc:
Wood from the Inazuman Cedar. It is soft, has straight veins, and gives off a light fragrance.
Can be used to create furnishings.

name: Otogi Wood
desc:
Wood from the Otogi Tree. It has just the right amount of moisture and oil, and as such has a great many uses.
Can be used to create furnishings.

name: Brightwood
desc:
Timber from the Brightwood Tree. It seems to have different properties from ordinary wood — soft but extremely resilient, easy to dye, and can be used for special purposes. 
Can be used to create furnishings.

name: Karmaphala Wood
desc:
The wood of the Karmaphala Tree. One can easily get a nice, smooth surface while working on this material and obtain a rather eye-pleasing result without going through any sophisticated processes.
Can be used to create furnishings.

name: Adhigama Wood
desc:
The wood of the Adhigama Tree. Can be found everywhere and therefore appears rather ordinary, but the wood is durable and easy to handle.
Can be used to create furnishings.

name: Mountain Date Wood
desc:
Wood of the Mountain Date Tree. Although it neither feels special to touch nor possesses a special texture, it retains water exceedingly well and is thus easy to grow.
Can be used to create furnishings.

name: Athel Wood
desc:
Wood of the Athel Tree. It has a special texture and is resilient to both drought and humidity, making it very durable.
Can be used to create furnishings.

name: Fabric
desc: Some fabric of fine make. It will surely be of use in making furnishings.

name: Red Dye
desc: Red dye. It will surely be of use in making furnishings.

name: Yellow Dye
desc: Yellow dye. It will surely be of use in making furnishings.

name: Blue Dye
desc: Blue dye. It will surely be of use in making furnishings.

name: A Piece of Paper
desc: You have no idea who slipped it to you.

name: Stolen Items
desc: Items belonging to the people of Mondstadt that were previously stolen by hilichurls in Drunkard Gorge.

name: Hilichurl Antidote
desc: Made by hilichurl witch doctors. Cures hilichurl poison.

name: Climbing Finish Line Garland
desc: Marker indicating the finish line of the Climbing Competition.

name: Gliding Finish Line Garland
desc: Marker indicating the finish line of the Gliding Competition.

name: Gliding Finish Line Garland
desc: Marker indicating the finish line of the Gliding Competition finals.

name: Gliding Champion Cup
desc: Awarded to the Mondstadt Gliding Competition Champion.

name: Jean's Document Package
desc: A few normal documents and a copy of Vera's Troubles.

name: Extreme Escape
desc: Musk's Travel Journal. In the notes regarding Musk Reef is a line that reads: "Only on a morning sea breeze can one glide here from Lover's Cape..."

name: Incomplete Score (Part 1)
desc: The first half of the sheet music for "Yellow." "S to J" is written in the bottom right corner.

name: Incomplete Score (Part 2)
desc: The second half of the sheet music for "Yellow."

name: Private Letter from Lisa to Jean
desc: Lisa has asked you to give this to Jean to deliver the news that Vera's Secret is receiving a sequel soon.

name: Autumn Night
desc: Tells a story in which a court mage and her King get married in the end.

name: Tasty-Looking Potion
desc: Looks tasty, but is actually a weakening potion.

name: Potion
desc: Lisa has asked you to give this to Barbara.

name: Barbara's Treatment
desc: Lisa has asked you to give this to Barbara.

name: Incomplete Poem (Part 1)
desc: The poem Venti asked you to look for, though only the first part of it.

name: Incomplete Poem (Part 2)
desc: The poem Venti asked you to look for, though it would seem there is more.

name: Incomplete Poem (Part 3)
desc: The poem Venti asked you to look for, piece the three pages together to reveal a love verselet.

name: Inscription Rubbing
desc: Ancient text engraved on the building.

name: Form Restoration Potion
desc: Can restore those that have been transformed into hilichurls by Abyss Mages back to their human form.

name: Holy Lyre der Himmel
desc: Can be used for taking down Stormterror.

name: Cricket Hair
desc: You didn't catch a cricket, just a hair off its leg.

name: Cricket (White)
desc: Common cricket. Can be seen everywhere, nothing rare about it at all.

name: Cricket (Blue)
desc: A big blue cricket. Seems to have a powerful bite force. Should be good at battle.

name: Cricket (Purple)
desc: A rare cricket with seven different red and purple layers to its wings.

name: Cricket (Gold)
desc: Oh, wow! The Legendary Golden Cricket!

name: Hydro Amber
desc: Hydro Amber given to you by Venti. Can be smashed to create rainfall. (Test)

name: Anemo Amber
desc: Anemo Amber given to you by Venti. Can be smashed to create air currents. (Test)

name: Random Loot (A)
desc: Items worth little value stolen from some random passer-by. Better return them quickly.

name: Random Loot (B)
desc: Items worth little value stolen from some random passer-by. Better return them quickly.

name: Random Loot (A)
desc: Items worth little value stolen from some random passer-by. Better return them quickly.

name: Random Loot (B)
desc: Items worth little value stolen from some random passer-by. Better return them quickly.

name: Crimson Crystal
desc: A teardrop crystal in which gloomy red gleams flow. Seems to have been left by the dragon. Perhaps the person that was talking with the dragon knows more about it, but where did he go?

desc: Seal Clue

name: Seal Clue 102
desc: Seal Clue

desc: Seal Clue

desc: Seal Clue

desc: Seal Clue

desc: Seal of Stormterror's Lair

name: Break the seal of Stormterror's Lair
desc: Seal of Stormterror's Lair

name: Fragmented Memory (Wind)
desc: Bring it close to your ear and it seems you can hear faint whispers, but can't make out what's being said. (Not available)

name: Sword Cemetery Seal 1
desc: Break Seal

name: Sword Cemetery Seal 2
desc: Break Seal

name: Sword Cemetery Seal 3
desc: Break Seal

name: Teardrop Crystal
desc: A curious teardrop left in the ancient arena that attracted hordes of monsters to fight for it.

name: Teardrop Crystal
desc: A teardrop looted and treasured by some members of the Eclipse hilichurl tribe. Had some trouble "convincing" them to part with it.

name: Teardrop Crystal
desc: A tear hidden in the forest ruins. Thankfully it hadn't been eaten by the insects.

name: Holy Lyre der Himmel
desc: A treasure that once belonged to Barbatos, the Anemo Archon, but its Anemo power has all dried up.

name: Partially Repaired Holy Lyre der Himmel
desc: A treasure that once belonged to Barbatos, the Anemo Archon, with some power restored by a Teardrop Crystal.

name: Completely Repaired Holy Lyre der Himmel
desc: A treasure that once belonged to Barbatos, the Anemo Archon, that has been restored to full power. Even Dvalin may heed its call.

name: Clear Dvalin Tear
desc: A teardrop left behind by Dvalin. The pure power of Anemo resonates within it.

name: Damaged Holy Lyre der Himmel
desc: A prized treasure of Barbatos, the Anemo Archon. Its clear sound that once echoed through the heavens and was beloved by the unruly Dvalin has now been reduced to naught but dull, ear-piercing noise.

name: Treasure Clue (I)
desc: A piece of paper with clues to a treasure. On it, is an unclear map with an unclear message.

name: Treasure Clue (II)
desc: A piece of paper with clues to a treasure. On it, is an unclear map with an unclear message.

name: Treasure Map
desc: A scribbled map with a simple marking in a particular area.

name: Hidden Key
desc: A key that once belonged to the Fatui. Just like all other keys, each respond to a door.

name: Black Key
desc: Opens the black door.

name: Vera's Melancholy (I)
desc:
I don't ever think the world is monotonous. It's just that interesting things happen in far away galaxies.
The great adventure of Vera, an ordinary girl always fascinated by distant lands, secretly begins.

name: Vera's Melancholy (II)
desc:
Everything's just boring. Everything, all the time. It's not depression. It's just reaching the age of 14.
So begins Vera's adventure.

name: Vera's Melancholy (III)
desc:
The Andromeda Empire stretches across half the galaxy group. Every planet within the Empire has its own demons and deities, dragons and monsters.
"I've come up with a story for every star from your home." "That's not possible. Looking from here, the Andromeda Galaxy is only one fifth the size of your moon."
So continues Vera's adventure.

name: Along with Divinity: Prologue
desc:
"Have you ever thought about what our lives would've been like without the archons?"
Come and join the author in an exploration of "divinity" with humor and logic.

name: The Legend of Vennessa (I)
desc: A popular song since the reconstruction of Mondstadt. It tells the story of Vennessa, the founder of the Knights of Favonius, in her early years as a slave in Mondstadt.

name: The Legend of Vennessa (II)
desc: A popular song since the reconstruction of Mondstadt. It tells the story of Vennessa, the founder of the Knights of Favonius, in her early years when she met Barbatos, the Anemo Archon, as well as how she defeated the drake and overthrew the Aristocrats.

name: Mondstadt General Goods Order Board
desc: Mondstadt General Goods Order Board

name: Cat's Tail Tavern Message Board
desc: Cat's Tail Tavern Message Board

name: The Fox in the Dandelion Sea (I)
desc:
"Dandelion, Dandelion, ride the wind to a faraway land," the Fox chants.
An unforgettable Mondstadt fairytale about a hunter and a fox. The Fox in the Dandelion Sea, an 11-part story, begins here.

name: The Fox in the Dandelion Sea (II)
desc:
"Be good and stay put." Trapped by a Mist Flower, what does fate have in store by the fox who met a hunter?
The story of the Hunter and the Fox continues in Part 2.

name: The Fox in the Dandelion Sea (III)
desc:
The Hunter of fruitless hunts was awoken by a commotion outside. Who is at his door?
The story of the Hunter and the Fox continues. The Fox in the Dandelion Sea, Part 3.

name: The Fox in the Dandelion Sea (V)
desc:
Upon accepting the Fox's conditions, he came to the place where all the prey who disappeared had eventually gone to — an endless field of dandelions.
The story of the Hunter and the Fox in the sea of dandelions. The Fox in the Dandelion Sea, Part 5.

name: The Fox in the Dandelion Sea (VI)
desc:
"Why do you want to learn the language of human?" "So I can befriend humans when I become one."
The child-like voice says, in the sea of dandelions. The Fox in the Dandelion Sea, Part 6.

name: The Fox in the Dandelion Sea (VII)
desc:
"Dandelion, Dandelion, ride the wind to a faraway land," the Fox chants.
Can the Hunter also learn magic to make his wish come true? The Fox in the Dandelion Sea, Part 7.

name: The Fox in the Dandelion Sea (X)
desc:
The somber parting has finally arrived... The Fox bids farewell to its mother, teacher, and the dandelion sea.
It's time to live up to the promise. The Fox in the Dandelion Sea, Part 10.

name: The Fox in the Dandelion Sea (XI)
desc:
"Dandelion, Dandelion, ride the wind to a faraway land," the Fox chants.
An unforgettable Mondstadt fairytale about a hunter and a fox. The Fox in the Dandelion Sea, the final installment.

name: Hilichurl Ballad Selection (I)
desc: The masterpiece of the Poet Laureate of Hilichurlian! Scholar Jacob Musk will show you the mysterious spiritual world of the hilichurls through this poetry collection!

name: Hilichurl Ballad Selection (II)
desc: Are wine and poetry a part of the hilichurl lifestyle? Do they have pure and devout desires? Expert on the hilichurls, Jacob Musk, is here to answer!

name: Vera's Melancholy (V)
desc:
You can't have picnics on the sides of a galactic highway! Even the deities will be held fully responsible for road accidents that might occur!
The doorway to a study in a simple village connects to anywhere in space and time! Having tea with the deities, playing hide-and-seek across time... Vera's great adventure continues!

name: Vera's Melancholy (IX)
desc:
"Vera's so beautiful, like a shining star in the universe, but I..." "Boys at this age are always more petite than girls of a similar age."
Childhood must be let go of to welcome the coming of the adolescent years. It's not too late to think about it now... Real melancholy finally hits Vera.

name: Vera's Melancholy (X)
desc:
"It's enough. Let's go home... The furthest place I've dreamt of, is the Delphi where you are."
Though the explanation is delayed, you should know that Delphi is the center of Greek mythology. Vera's Melancholy - the perfect ending... or is it?

name: Breeze Amidst the Forest - Ballad Selection Excerpt
desc: A collection of Mondstadt ballads, recorded, compiled and arranged by scholars centuries ago.

name: The Boar Princess (I)
desc:
A long, long time ago, in the forest kingdom... What legends occurred there?
The Boar Princess, Part 1. A story about friendship, love, and death.

name: The Boar Princess (II)
desc:
A lifeless ice field, a land even the gentle Anemo Archon has never visited. How is it that it still has its lonely inhabitants?
The Boar Princess, Part 2. The story continues on the glacier.

name: The Boar Princess (III)
desc:
"Now and evermore shall you be bereft of hope." What fate awaits the wolf pup who bears such a cruel curse?
The Boar Princess, Part 3.

name: The Boar Princess (IV)
desc:
The wolf pup grew up in the cold loneliness. The secret past of the lone wolf is now revealed.
The Boar Princess, Part 4.

name: The Boar Princess (V)
desc:
"No one deserves this fate." The good princess sheds a tear of compassion. For those who persevere as true companions, even the ice shall melt before their determination.
The Boar Princess, Part 5.

name: The Boar Princess (VII)
desc:
All the sacrifices made out in the frozen plains were not in vain. The perfect ending of friendship, love, life and death!
This is the end to the famous and touching story, The Boar Princess.

name: The Mondstadt Tower (I)
desc:
In the age of depression and tyranny, the outlander girl met the ominous orphan. Does this fateful encounter foretell a tragic ending?
The historic romance novel, The Mondstadt Tower, begins!

name: Gliding Instruction Manual
desc: A guidebook for the ones new to using wind gliders. It also serves as a mandatory reading material to get a gliding license in Mondstadt. It contains all the necessary info any user must know.

name: Elemental Mark
desc: Overly Clean Cut

name: Broken-off Branch
desc: Seems it's been rotten for a long time.

name: Fabric Piece
desc: Wonder who left it behind?

name: Breeze Amidst the Forest Supplement: The Dragon Tome
desc:
A supplement to the "Breeze Amidst the Forest" ballad selection with excerpts from various sources.
It tells the story of the Dragon of Mondstadt.

name: Letter from the Abyss Order
desc: Seems to be a declaration of war from the Abyss Order to the "Darknight Hero." Many key phrases have been redacted.

name: The Pale Princess and the Six Pygmies (I)
desc: A fairytale story that has been told throughout Teyvat for ages. This is part one, which tells the story of the Land of Night and the Moonlight Forest.

name: The Pale Princess and the Six Pygmies (II)
desc: A fairytale story that has been told throughout Teyvat for ages. This installment tells of the meeting of the Pale Princess and the Light Prince.

name: The Pale Princess and the Six Pygmies (III)
desc: A fairytale story that has been told throughout Teyvat for ages. This installment tells of the Pale Princess and the Light Prince's decision to save the Moonlight Forest.

name: The Pale Princess and the Six Pygmies (IV)
desc: A fairytale story that has been told throughout Teyvat for ages. Installment four describes the meeting between the Pale Princess, the Light Prince, and the Six Pygmies.

name: The Pale Princess and the Six Pygmies (V)
desc: A fairytale story that has been told throughout Teyvat for ages. In this installment, the Six Pygmies' sinister scheme starts to unfold.

name: The Pale Princess and the Six Pygmies (VI)
desc: A fairytale story that has been told throughout Teyvat for ages. This installment tells of how the Six Pygmies managed to implement their nefarious plot.

name: The Pale Princess and the Six Pygmies (VII)
desc: A fairytale story that has been told throughout Teyvat for ages. The final installment brings everything to a conclusion, and includes the Night Mother's prophecy.

name: 1000 Years of Loneliness
desc: The beginning of the Springvale Hunter's tragic fantasy journey. Where did misfortune first befall him? What marks the start and finish of the 1000-year journey of loneliness? Let this first volume of 1000 Years of Loneliness be your guide through the fantastical fog that is the life of Gothson.

name: Teyvat Travel Guide - Mondstadt
desc: A magazine by the Adventurers' Guild. Each issue introduces great sceneries across Teyvat. This issue includes a short traveling diary of Alice the Traveler on her experiences in Mondstadt.

name: Wind, Courage, and Wings
desc: A book mistakenly taken by Amber... about fables?

name: Hunting Trap
desc: Used to trap beasts of a certain size. If you pay attention in the wilds to collect them, you can make one like this. Set one down, and then conceal it carefully.

name: Diary of Roald the Adventurer: Qingce Village
desc: A diary left behind by the famed adventurer, Roald, at a makeshift camp. It stills looks new, and smells like the fragrant herbs of Mt. Qingce.

name: Diary of Roald the Adventurer: Luhua Pool
desc: A diary left behind by the famed adventurer, Roald, at a makeshift camp. It seems to have been dipped in water, with the watermark of a fox's footprint.

name: Diary of Roald the Adventurer: Yaoguang Shoal
desc: A diary left behind by the famed adventurer, Roald. The pages smell like the sea breeze.

name: Letter for Dongdong
desc: A letter treasured by Dongdong from Qingce Village. It seems to be a letter from his father.

name: Someone's Diary I: Yaoguang Shoal
desc: A diary left behind by someone in the wilderness that tells of the owner's unfortunate encounters at Yaoguang Shoal.

name: Someone's Diary II: Guili Plains
desc: A diary left behind by someone in the wilderness that tells of the owner's unfortunate encounters at Guili Plains.

name: Someone's Diary III: Jueyun Karst
desc: A diary left behind by someone in the wilderness that tells of the owner's adventures at Jueyun Karst.

name: Someone's Diary IV: Liyue Harbor
desc: A diary left behind by someone in Liyue that tells of the owner's adventures there.

name: Scattered Page
desc: (TEST) Adventure Journal Page

name: Intact Tome
desc: (TEST) Adventure Journal

name: "Of Mountains and Seas"
desc: Notes penned by Leonard, an adventurer from the distant past. Clearly an ancient text, it has suffered much wear and tear. Most of the content has been lost to the ravages of time, with just a few fragments remaining.

name: Draft Manuscript of "Hyakunin Ikki: The Greatest Battle"
Hearty Mushrooms
desc: Hardy common fungi. Can grow anywhere with the right amount of shade and moisture.

name: Crunchy Carrots
desc: A healthy and nutritious vegetable that is crunchy and sweet to the taste. Easy to grow and harvest.

name: A Plump Cabbage
desc: A layered, leafy vegetable. Said to have originally been an ornamental plant, it certainly looks great in the pot.

name: Azurite
desc: A piece of plaustrite dug up from the roots of a Bloatty Floatty. It has a rather unique color and is, perhaps, the Azurite that Wang'ya spoke of...

name: Vermillionite
desc: A piece of plaustrite plucked from a Ruin Hunter. It has a rather unique color and is, perchance, the Vermillionite that Wang'ya mentioned...

name: Letter to the Treasure Hoarders
desc: A letter written by someone to the Treasure Hoarders about some plans for the Lantern Rite...

name: Nephrite Ring
desc: A Nephrite Ring obtained from a slime. Gorgeous color and clearly a top-quality item. This must be Mr. Zhu's lost property.

name: Delicious Golden Crab
desc: Crab meat that's been rolled in flour, deep fried, and then pan fried together with ginger and garlic. When you finally plate up, the crab appears to be lying on gold.

name: Wyatt's Red Key
desc: A key to the warehouse's gates kept by Wyatt. The likeliness of him losing it is next to him losing his slim wallet.

name: Wyatt's Black Key
desc: A key to the warehouse's gates kept by Wyatt. The likeliness of him losing it is next to him losing his slim wallet.

name: Coin Pouch
desc: A small coin pouch of Mora that doesn't weigh much; you'd sometimes forget it's even there.

name: Meal Fee Pouch
desc: A small coin pouch of Mora that contains payment for a meal ordered at the Good Hunter. Do not take your cut out of this bag.

name: Delicious Sticky Honey Roast
desc: A meat dish in a sweet honey sauce. The warm honey draws out the flavor of the meat, creating a flavor explosion akin to bathing in the warm summer sun.

name: Sturdy Plank
desc: A sturdy plank. It feels heavy and reliable, and easy to apply to all sorts of scenarios.

name: Fragile Wooden Plank
desc: A fragile wooden plank that is easily breakable. It doesn't serve much of a purpose aside from pretending that you're strong.

name: A Bundle of Ropes
desc: A bundle of sturdy ropes long enough to temporarily hold certain things together for a time, however short it may be.

name: Meal Fee Pouch
desc: A small coin pouch of Mora that contains payment for a meal ordered at the Good Hunter. Do not take your cut out of this bag.

name: Lost Coin Pouch
desc: A small coin pouch of Mora that doesn't weigh much; you'd sometimes forget it's even there.

name: Meal Fee Pouch
desc: A small coin pouch of Mora that contains payment for a meal ordered at the Good Hunter. Do not take your cut out of this bag.

name: Delicious Fried Radish Balls
desc: Fried Radish Balls. It's insane that something so delicious comes from plain old radishes! All who eat them will truly understand Liyue's culinary reputation.

name: Delicious Calla Lily Seafood Soup
desc: A balanced combination of seafood. The crab, mint, and Calla Lily come together perfectly to dance on your tongue. It reminds you of playing barefoot by the lake in summer.

name: Bag of Goods
desc: A bag that is quite heavy. Once picked up, you can't help but think of asking someone else for a hand.

name: Processed Noctilucous Jade
desc: TEST Processed Noctilucous Jade

name: "Mondstadt Sunset"
desc: A pretty and sweet cocktail. The juice slowly sinks in the clear liquor like the sunset. A favorite among couples.

name: "Margaret"
desc: Margaret's refreshing signature cocktail, popular among those who only want one drink. It also uses dandelions, but the greatest difference between this and dandelion wine is the price.

name: "Charged Attack"
desc: A straight liquor shot, giving you the original taste of the distilled liquor itself. One shot is enough to make your body burn.

name: "Pearl"
desc: A mellow beer with thick layer of foam on top. The flying bubbles from making toasts gave it its name.

name: Messy "Mondstadt Sunset"
desc: Though the taste is acceptable, but it has lost its aesthetic value due to a mistake in the making.

name: Unusual "Margaret"
desc: It looks alright, but a mistake in the making cost it its refreshing taste.

name: Bizarre "Charged Attack"
desc: A shot without the taste of the distilled liquor and pretty much anything else... Something must have gone wrong.

name: Unusual "Pearl"
desc: Though the taste is acceptable, but a mistake in the making cost it its texture.

name: Odd Cocktail
desc: A fruity cocktail, but it somehow tastes different from what Quinn described.

name: Messy Cocktail
desc: A drink with a messy taste, definitely not what Margaret promised.

name: Bizarre Cocktail
desc: There are tastes of different liquors aside from the distilled liquor... This is not what Draff wanted.

name: Unusual Beer
desc: There are bubbles and foams, sure, but it somehow tastes different from what Jack described.

name: Barely Drinkable Cocktail
desc: Due to mistakes made while adding ingredients, this wine has undergone some unpleasant changes...

name: Unknown Cocktail
desc: A cocktail never before seen. Kinda makes one wanna try.

name: Plain Liquor
desc: A common alcoholic drink available anywhere.

name: Godwin's Letter
desc: A love letter from Godwin to Glory detailing their love and the intimate things they did, which would make any reader blush. However, only the last part is somewhat memorable.

name: Someone's Drifting Bottle
desc: A hefty bottle that came drifting with the waves, carrying tokens of an old friendship and the hopes of being reunited.

name: Tunner's Cough Syrup
desc: Cough Syrup made from Sweet Flower that can moderately suppress cough. Due to its sweet and refreshing taste, the syrup is very popular among kids in Mondstadt. Some kids even wish they had a cough so they can get the syrup.

name: Draff's Letter
desc: A letter from Draff to Sister Grace. It was tightly sealed, but it wasn't enough to withstand the brute force of the hilichurls.

name: Materials for Training Dummy
desc: All sorts of materials. These should be just enough to make a training dummy.

name: Sara's Letter
desc: A thick-set letter sent back from Liyue Harbor to Sara. Several feathers are still stuck in the envelope, signifying the effort that carrier pigeon put in and the sort of treatment it received.

name: Clean Radish
desc: Rich in fiber and nutrients. Easy to grow and harvest.

name: (TEST) Klee's Notebook
desc: (TEST) Klee's Notebook

name: Guy's Letter
desc: A letter from Guy to his father sealed as per regulation of the Knights of Favonius. It is tightly sealed to deter influence of rain and perplexity.

name: Quinn's Special
desc: A list of ingredients Quinn needs for his cocktail. If other ingredients are used, what kind of result could one expect?

name: Margaret's Special
desc: A list of ingredients Margaret needs for her cocktail. If other ingredients are used, what kind of result could one expect?

name: Jack's Special
desc: A list of ingredients Jack needs for his cocktail. If other ingredients are used, what kind of result could one expect?

name: Draff's Special
desc: A list of ingredients Draff needs for his cocktail. If other ingredients are used, what kind of result could one expect?

name: Teyvat Travel Guide - Liyue
desc: A magazine by the Adventurers' Guild. Each issue introduces great sceneries across Teyvat. This issue includes a short traveling diary of Alice the Traveler in Liyue.

name: Letter
desc: A letter written by Xingqiu to the Feiyun Commerce Guild. The handwriting is so messy its barely recognizable.

name: A Huge Bag of Mora
desc: A heavy bag full of Mora provided by the Feiyun Commerce Guild. Enough to purchase every Cor Lapis available in Liyue.

name: Legend of the Shattered Halberd (VI)
desc:
Mir once again chanted the forgotten spell. The maiden was reunited with him again. "So, this is what you truly look like."
"The world is beyond repair. It shall be born anew from the ashes of the last." The mad Celestial Emperor sentenced all living things of the world to a harsh punishment.
"But you, you would understand me, wouldn't you?" The nameless thief who stole the national treasure said to his lord.
"No. No apologies necessary, for you are benevolent."

name: Intact Training Dummy
desc: An intact training dummy. Very sturdy, perfect for training.

name: Legend of the Geo Archon: God of the Stove
desc: Stories about the Geo Archon as the God of the Stove.

name: Legend of the Geo Archon: The Groundbreaker
desc: Stories about the Geo Archon and his divine duties as The Groundbreaker.

name: Legend of the Geo Archon: God of Wealth
desc: Stories about the Geo Archon and his divine duties as the God of Wealth.

name: Legend of the Geo Archon: God of History
desc: Stories about the Geo Archon and his divine duties as the God of History.

name: The Wrath of Haishan
desc: Segments from "The Wrath of Haishan," mentioned by Liu Su, that features the story of The Crux...

name: Ring of Raining Blades (I)
desc: Segments from "Ring of Raining Blades (I)," mentioned by Liu Su, that features the story of the Guhua Clan...

name: Ring of Raining Blades (II)
desc: Segments from "Ring of Raining Blades (II)," mentioned by Liu Su, that features the story of the Guhua Clan...

name: Meal Box by Smiley Yanxiao for Jiangxue
desc: A tightly sealed meal box. It's quite heavy, it must contain quite a big portion.

name: A log of ships coming in and out by Little Lulu
desc: An elegantly-written note by Little Lulu. It reads, "1 ship came into Liyue Harbor yesterday morning."

name: A log of ships coming in and out by Little Lulu
desc: An elegantly-written note by Little Lulu. It reads, "2 ships came into Liyue Harbor yesterday morning."

name: A log of ships coming in and out by Little Lulu
desc: An elegantly-written note by Little Lulu. It reads, "No ships came in or out of Liyue Harbor yesterday morning."

name: A log of ships coming in and out by Little Fei
desc: A scribbled note by Little Fei. It reads, "1 ship sailed out of Liyue Harbor yesterday at noon."

name: A log of ships coming in and out by Little Fei
desc: A scribbled note by Little Fei. It reads "2 ships sailed into Liyue Harbor yesterday at noon."

name: A log of ships coming in and out by Little Fei
desc: A scribbled note by Little Fei. It reads "3 ships sailed into Liyue Harbor yesterday at noon."

name: A log of ships coming in and out by Little Meng
desc: A neatly-written note by Little Meng. It reads, "No ships sailed in or out of Liyue Harbor last night."

name: A log of ships coming in and out by Little Meng
desc: A neatly-written note by Little Meng. It reads, "1 ship sailed out of Liyue Harbor last night."

name: A log of ships coming in and out by Little Meng
desc: A neatly-written note by Little Meng. It reads, "3 ships sailed into Liyue Harbor last night."

name: Sealed Package
desc: A heavy and tightly sealed packaged with a novel written by Chang the Ninth. It seems that he doesn't want people to read his works...

name: First Apprentice of Guhua
desc: A novel by Chang the Ninth. Its thickness and weight say much about the effort he put in.

name: Diary of Roald the Adventurer: Guyun Stone Forest
desc: A diary left behind by the famed adventurer, Roald, by chance. The pages are damp and seem to have been soaked in water.

name: Diary of Roald the Adventurer: Sal Terrae
desc: A diary left behind by the famed adventurer, Roald. The pages are littered with a small amount of shiny but bitter salt crystals.

name: Diary of Roald the Adventurer: Qingyun Peak, Jueyun Karst
desc: A diary left behind by the famed adventurer, Roald. The pages have the scent of flowers that grow on cliffs.

name: Diary of Roald the Adventurer: Aocang Lake, Jueyun Karst
desc: A diary of the famed adventurer, Roald, left by the lake. It tells of his plans after his adventures on Mt. Aocang.

name: Treasure Map of Lone Gorge
desc: A treasure map obtained from Bolai of a hidden treasure somewhere out there...

name: Treasure Map of Lone Gorge
desc: A treasure map obtained from Bolai of a hidden treasure somewhere out there...

name: Treasure Map of Lone Gorge
desc: A treasure map obtained from Bolai of a hidden treasure somewhere out there...

name: Poorly-Sealed Box
desc: A box that's carelessly sealed. The content doesn't seem important.

name: Tightly-Sealed Box
desc: A box that's tightly sealed. The content must be important...

name: Katheryne's Letter
desc: A tightly-sealed letter packed with other supporting documents that prove the bearer of the letter to be a reliable and experienced adventurer.

name: Records of Jueyun: Stone Beasts
desc: A collection of folk stories, myths, and legends from Liyue. It's quite a page-turner. This segment is on the legends of stone beasts.

name: Records of Jueyun: Palace Beneath the Sea
desc: A collection of folk stories, myths, and legends from Liyue. It's quite a page-turner. This segment is on ancient fictional stories.

name: Verses of Equilibrium
desc: Legend has that it contains ancient incantations used to pay respects to Rex Lapis and the yaksha adepti. It also serves as a historical record of the ancient belief in the Geo Archon.

name: Records of the Gallant: The Hermit
desc: A compilation of stories and legends of various knights-errant in Liyue. Some of them have been told for a long time but are still popular among the people.

name: Customs of Liyue: Flower Ball
desc: A book on the cultures and customs of Liyue originally compiled by Fadhlan, a scholar from Sumeru residing in Liyue. It was then edited by many local scholars and published. It is one of the bestsellers in Liyue.

name: Stone Tablet Compilations: Vol. I
desc: A history book compiled and translated from ancient stone tablets of Liyue by the historian Zichang. It contains various fragmented historical events.

name: Humor From Tianheng
desc: A poetry collection by Pingshan, The Mystic. The quality of the poems is all over the place, but it has long been a reference book for young poets or poet-wannabes in Liyue.

name: Hilichurl Cultural Customs (I)
desc: It contains the investigations and observations into the cultural customs of the hilichurls by the "Poet Laureate of Hilichurlian," Jacob Musk, a Mondstadt ecologist. This volume features the social structure and characteristics of the hilichurls.

name: Hilichurl Cultural Customs (II)
desc: It contains the investigations and observations into the cultural customs of the hilichurls by the "Poet Laureate of Hilichurlian," Jacob Musk, a Mondstadt ecologist. This volume features the beliefs and spiritual world of the hilichurls.

name: Hilichurl Cultural Customs (IV)
desc: It contains the investigations and observations into the cultural customs of the hilichurls by the "Poet Laureate of Hilichurlian," Jacob Musk, a Mondstadt ecologist. This volume explores the diverse cultural customs of the hilichurls in relation to Mondstadt's.

name: History of Kings and Clans: Prologue
desc: A comprehensive history of Mondstadt edited and compiled by the Northland History Society.

name: Biography of Gunnhildr
desc: A history book on the life of the apical ancestor of the Gunnhildr Clan compiled by Eckhart Gunnhildr, a modern historian of Mondstadt. It consists of fragmented stories and legends from the aristocratic period.

name: Ballads of the Squire (I)
desc: Ballads that have been passed down since the aristocratic period and are said to come from Ragnvindr the Dawn Knight himself. They tell of Ragnvindr's days as a knight's squire.

name: Ballads of the Squire (II)
desc: Ballads that have been passed down since the aristocratic period and are said to come from Ragnvindr the Dawn Knight himself. They tell of Ragnvindr's friendship with a sword-dancer.

name: Teyvat Wilderness Survivalist's Recipes
desc: Field-cooking skills are paramount to surviving in the wilderness. Lynn, a 10-year Adventurers' Guild veteran, teaches you how to cook delicious and fulfilling food in times of emergency in the wilderness!

name: Treasure Map of Giant's Steps
desc: A treasure map obtained from Bolai of a hidden treasure somewhere out there...

desc: A treasure map obtained from Bolai of a hidden treasure somewhere out there...

desc: A treasure map obtained from Bolai of a hidden treasure somewhere out there...
