There is neither soil nor water inside the Ruin Golem. It must be a nightmarish place for Ararycan.

name: Araesha's Flower
desc:
A flower gifted to you by Araesha.
The biggest mystery is perhaps why Araesha describes the riddles as being "delicious"... Is it because they are all about food?

name: Arakara's Flower
desc:
A flower gifted to you by Arakara.
For Arakara, who nurtures Viparyas, flowers given to friends must be most precious indeed.

name: The Siblings' Flowers
desc:
Flowers gifted by Arapacati and her brothers.
Longing to be connected as "siblings" are, these Aranara have each taken on the role of sister or brother. Their obsession with cooking stems from the wish to share food with family.
That being said, an Aranara's tastebuds are not to be trusted.

name: The Song Gatherers' Flowers
desc:
Flowers gifted to you by the Song Gatherers.
"No matter how dark the sky and land get, as long as your spirit emits warm, golden light like the sun, there will always be hope."

name: Aralila and Aranishat's Flowers
desc:
Flowers gifted by Aralila and Aranishat.
We ourselves are the strongest. Of that, there is no doubt!

name: Arakanta's Flower
desc:
A flower gifted by Arakanta.
Arakanta used to love hanging out with Rishboland Tigers. But now, he has created a new game for his Nara friend.

name: Stories of You and the Aranara
desc: So many wonderful things transpired during your adventures with the Aranara. In the world of the Aranara where stories are highly valued, maybe someone is willing to "exchange" these with you.

name: "Emergency Adjustment Plan"
desc: This map was contained within the plans that a Fatuus named Oleg accidentally dropped. All the encampment positions and Fatui patrol routes have been marked out here.

name: Asterism Shard
desc: A mysterious shard engraved with a pattern of stars. It seems to be the key to solving a certain mechanism puzzle somewhere.

name: Key
desc: A key that you found near the mysterious plant. This may be used to open a certain door in a high-up location within Xinyan's Mirage.

name: Bottle of Spring Water
desc: A bottle of spring water. The Glacial Spring Water that Blazing Heart desires should be stored within.

name: Frozen Soul's Petal
desc:
An uncanny petal. At first glance, it seems like ice molded into the shape of a petal, but it is quite soft to the touch.
"Plant my petal at the ending point of the intersection of melodies, and what had once sunk into the earth will re-emerge with the music."
That's what Frozen Soul said.

name: Elegantly-Written Note
desc: An elegantly-written note.

name: A Letter
desc: A letter.

name: Rock Garden Rough Stone (Left)
desc: Mountain rocks. They look suited in all ways to be used as base materials from which to carve rocks for the bonsai's left side.

name: Rock Garden Rough Stone (Right)
desc: Mountain rocks. They look suited in all ways to be used as base materials from which to carve rocks for the bonsai's right side.

name: Rock Garden Carving Tools
desc: Carving tools that you found on the Mondstadt-style mountains. You might be able to use them to carve the base materials you have into a rock garden.

name: Rock Garden Carving Tools
desc: Carving tools that you found on the Inazuma-style mountains. You might be able to use them to carve the base materials you have into a rock garden.

name: Small Gear
desc: A small gear. No matter how small a gear is, it can be of use sometime, perhaps?

name: Medium Gear
desc: A medium gear. "The pivotal one," as we call it.

name: Drive Gear
desc: A gear that can transmit a measure of force. After all, momentum is key.

name: Large Gear
desc: A large gear. Its weight and the noise it emits will make an impression for sure.

name: Duplex Gear
desc: A rather small duplex gear. Double the flanks, double the labor hours.

name: Large Duplex Gear
desc: A fairly large duplex gear. The bigger the size is, the more it takes to manufacture.

name: Driven Gear
desc: A gear that requires power to rotate. It can be very helpful. Really. Can someone help rotate it, please?

name: Leisurely Rocks: Left
desc: Slightly soft bonsai rocks. They seem to be able to summon a leisurely and comfy breeze. These can be placed on the left side of the bonsai.

name: Leisurely Rocks: Right
desc: Slightly soft bonsai rocks. They seem to be able to summon a leisurely and comfy breeze. These can be placed on the right side of the bonsai.

name: Hoverlight Rocks: Left
desc: Rocks of moderate hardness. It is said that a glimmer will dance across the surface of these rocks during stormy weather. These can be placed on the left side of the bonsai.

name: Hoverlight Rocks: Right
desc: Bonsai rocks of moderate hardness. It is said that a glimmer will dance across the surface of these rocks during stormy weather. These can be placed on the right side of the bonsai.

name: Unyielding Rocks: Left
desc: Very hard bonsai rocks that have an air of firmness to them. These can be placed on the left side of the bonsai.

name: Unyielding Rocks: Right
desc: Very hard bonsai rocks that have an air of firmness to them. These can be placed on the right side of the bonsai.

name: Living Spring
desc: Water obtained from the source of the rivers flowing across Apam Woods. According to Arapas, soup made from such spring water is a Supreme Delicacy. But one wonders if it really is any different from ordinary water...

name: A Box of Components
desc: A box full of components. They all look quite intact, perhaps because monsters have no interest in them...

name: Note of Unknown Origin: I
desc: You found this note in the mysterious space. Its content seems similar to that of a journal.

name: Note of Unknown Origin: II
desc: You found this note in the mysterious space. Its content seems similar to that of a journal.

name: Note of Unknown Origin: III
desc: You found this note in the mysterious space. Its content seems similar to that of a journal.

name: Note of Unknown Origin: IV
desc: You found this note in the mysterious space. Its content seems similar to that of a journal.

name: A Note
desc: A wrinkled note with horrendously slanted handwriting.

name: Redemption Voucher 1
desc: Used to redeem Mirrorpool Horned Owl: Turning

name: Redemption Voucher 2
desc: Used to redeem Mirrorpool Horned Owl: Dancing

name: Redemption Voucher 3
desc: Used to redeem Mirrorpool Horned Owl: Air Time

name: Redemption Voucher 4
desc: Used to redeem Thundering Horned Owl: Turning

desc: Used to redeem Thundering Horned Owl: Dancing

desc: Used to redeem Thundering Horned Owl: Air Time

desc: Used to redeem Traveling Horned Owl

desc: Used to redeem Thundering Triped: Jiggy

name: Redemption Voucher 19
desc: Used to redeem Flowfire Triped: Sitting

name: Redemption Voucher 20
desc: Used to redeem Traveling Triped

name: Part: Breeze
desc: A part of the "Evermotion Mechanical Painting" that Félix Yogue is trying to restore.

name: Part: Sky
desc: A part of the "Evermotion Mechanical Painting" that Félix Yogue is trying to restore.

name: Part: Clouds
desc: A part of the "Evermotion Mechanical Painting" that Félix Yogue is trying to restore.

name: Part: Company
desc: A part of the "Evermotion Mechanical Painting" that Félix Yogue is trying to restore.

name: Part: Lonely
desc: A part of the "Evermotion Mechanical Painting" that Félix Yogue is trying to restore.

name: Part: Meadow
desc: A part of the "Evermotion Mechanical Painting" that Félix Yogue is trying to restore.

name: Forensic Office Research Log Excerpt
desc: A research log excerpt with plenty of crinkles. The handwriting is still very much legible.

name: Note of Unknown Origin
desc: You found this note in the mysterious space. Its content seems similar to that of a journal.

name: Crystalline Core
desc: The crystalline core component that was missing from the curious Fatui machine. According to Persikov's manuscript, the machine can be restarted if three such cores are found and inserted into the device.

name: Crystalline Core
desc: The crystalline core component that was missing from the curious Fatui machine. According to Persikov's manuscript, the machine can be restarted if three such cores are found and inserted into the device.

name: Crystalline Core
desc: The crystalline core component that was missing from the curious Fatui machine. According to Persikov's manuscript, the machine can be restarted if three such cores are found and inserted into the device.

name: Old Yellowed Notes
desc: Old Yellowed Notes

name: Mysterious Letter
desc: Mysterious Letter

name: A Seemingly Waterproof Note
desc: A Seemingly Waterproof Note

name: Reverberating Key
desc: A key related to a certain mysterious plant. It seems to be able to open some door somewhere...

name: A New Letter
desc:
A letter the head housemaid, Adelinde, just received. It needs to be sent to Dawn Winery for archiving.
The paper is slightly wrinkled. Maybe the person who wrote the letter was in a hurry and couldn't find a desk.

name: Dawn Winery's Top-Quality Grape Juice
desc:
A gift from Diluc. A bottle of grape juice with luxury packaging. It is something Paimon has long been looking forward to, but more so a memento of the time when you and your friends handled the crisis together.
It is also Diluc's personal favorite, produced using only Dawn Winery's best quality grapes.
Being "Master Diluc's favorite grape juice" seems to have inestimable commercial value...

name: Slime Condensate-Soaked Soil
desc: Soil soaked with Slime Condensate. What will Akim use this sticky stuff for?

name: Whopperflower Root Soil
desc: Soil collected from Whopperflower roots. What will Akim use it for?

name: Moist Soil
desc: Moist soil collected from the bottom of rocks. What will Akim use it for?

name: Starlight Coalescence
desc: A translucent crystal that seems to hold coalescent starlight within it. This item seems to be key to solving a certain mechanism puzzle somewhere.

name: Dragonspine Supplies: Ham
desc: Ham meant to be used for resupply. It will keep longer in low-temperature conditions.

name: Nightwatch Contract
desc: A contract penned and signed personally by the Prinzessin der Verurteilung herself. It may be used to authorize the opening of the navigational site. Those who should produce this letter of warrant shall be authorized forthwith to spread their black feathers where dawn meets dusk, and envelop the skies in night's own embrace.

name: Special "Concresoil" for Toys
desc: Special "Concresoil" Akim made for Nima. What kind of pot warriors will Nima make with it?

name: Whopperflower Root Soil
desc: Soil collected from Whopperflower roots. What will Akim use it for?

name: Fertile Soil (Reportedly)
desc:
You can't tell whether this soil is fertile or not.
What will Akim use this for?

name: Discarded "Concresoil"
desc: "Concresoil" of poor quality. It looks to be in terrible condition...

name: Tenryou Commission's Missing Person Poster
desc: An official missing person poster with the Tenryou Commission's symbol on it.

name: Sea Salt-Crusted Key
desc: A key found in the Golden Apple Archipelago, seemingly able to open a lock somewhere...

name: Special Bird Egg
desc: A bird egg needed for making Angler Kayvan's special bait. This special egg was collected from a specific tree, but it does not look particularly special.

name: Special Mushroom
desc: A mushroom needed for making Angler Kayvan's special bait. For some reason, mushrooms of this kind hold some appeal for monsters such that they would willingly collect them...

name: Special Mint
desc: Mint needed for making Angler Kayvan's special bait. For some reason, mints of this kind hold some appeal for monsters such that they would willingly collect them...

name: Special Harra Fruit
desc: Harra Fruit needed for making Angler Kayvan's special bait. For some reason, Harra Fruits of this kind hold some appeal for monsters such that they would willingly collect them...

name: Special Sweet Flower
desc: Sweet Flower needed for making Angler Kayvan's special bait. For some reason, Sweet Flowers of this kind hold some appeal for monsters such that they would willingly collect them...

name: Box Lunch from Tighnari
desc: Emergency food that Tighnari prepared for Haypasia. Paimon took a peek into the lunchbox, finding some traditional Sumeru delicacies that looked very tasty inside.

name: Letter to Haypasia
desc: A letter from Tighnari to Haypasia. In the letter, Tighnari explains your identity and situation after coming to Sumeru and requests that Haypasia help clear up your doubts.

name: Box Lunch from the Traveler
desc: Food that you have specifically prepared for Haypasia. The box contains Sweet Madame and Radish Veggie Soup. You hope Haypasia will like it.

name: Tighnari's Introduction Letter
desc:
A letter from Tighnari to Rohawi, a researcher from Amurta. In the letter, Tighnari requests that Rohawi use his prowess in collecting information to help you.
Rohawi's address in Sumeru City is also attached therein.

name: Bag of Transaction Funds
desc: A bag of Mora given by Alhaitham for purchasing Canned Knowledge. You can feel the heavy weight of the bag.

name: Package of Canned Knowledge
desc: Canned Knowledge purchased at Dori's booth with the Mora given to you by Alhaitham. Packaged as common commodities to keep it low-key.

name: Canned Knowledge "Swordfighting Techniques VIII"
desc: Canned Knowledge labeled "Swordfighting Techniques VIII." It was bought from Dori's booth at the price of 100,000 Mora at Paimon's instigation. You have no idea where the first seven in the series are, but things like "Combat Techniques" will always be useful. Well, probably.

name: Bag of Intel Transaction Funds
desc: A bag of Mora provided by Alhaitham for buying the intel on the whereabouts of the Divine Knowledge Capsule.

name: Picture of the Transaction
desc:
A picture of a scene where the "Divine Knowledge Capsule" is being traded.
In the picture, there is Mizri, the leader of Ayn Al-Ahmar, and the Divine Knowledge Capsule giving off a red glow in his hand.

name: Informant Code Chart
desc:
A code chart given to you by Alhaitham. Seems like whoever seeks to purchase "special commodities" from Dori has to provide the right code first.
Check this code chart before visiting Dori's contact, just in case.

name: Misplaced Conch 1
desc: This Imaging Conch should have been placed somewhere else but was abandoned here by someone, causing it to project images out of their proper order. Return it to its rightful place, and who knows what you might find...

name: Misplaced Conch 2
desc: This Imaging Conch should have been placed somewhere else but was abandoned here by someone, causing it to project images out of their proper order. Return it to its rightful place, and who knows what you might find...

name: Misplaced Conch 3
desc: This Imaging Conch should have been placed somewhere else but was abandoned here by someone, causing it to project images out of their proper order. Return it to its rightful place, and who knows what you might find...

name: Prescription Medication from Bimarstan for Gurgen
desc: Medication prescribed for Gurgen. It should be taken along with abundant rest.

name: Prescription Medication from Bimarstan for Azra
desc: Medication prescribed for Azra. It smells incredibly bitter.

name: Prescription Medication from Bimarstan for Aftab
desc: Medication prescribed for Aftab. Taker of this medication needs to practice a bland diet.

name: Fresh Harra Fruit
desc: Harra Fruit needed for making Angler Kayvan's special bait. For some reason, Harra Fruits of this kind have an appeal to monsters. They would often linger around areas where these Harra Fruits are...

name: Fresh Zaytun Peach
desc: A special Zaytun Peach needed for making Angler Kayvan's special bait. It seems nothing different than a regular Zaytun Peach.

name: "The Best Water"
desc: Water collected in Vanarana, clear, cold, and refreshing — a leaf falling on top of it would look as if floating in the air. This is transparent water of extraordinary quality.

name: Silver Pocket Watch
desc: This is certainly not a new pocket watch. But you can tell that it has been carefully polished, evidence of how much the owner really cares about it. Inside is a photograph centering on a young girl from Snezhnaya.

name: Old Insignia
desc: This looks like a Fatui insignia, but it's all scratched up somehow.

name: Fresh Slime Condensate
desc: Slime Condensate that looks really fresh. Who knows what Garcia needs it for...

name: Sareh's Note
desc: This time, we are looking for a kitten named Lale with black and white fur. If you wish to call for Lale's attention in cat language, you need to say "Meow, meow meow meow—" with the tone going downward then upward, before ending on an even higher note.

name: Sareh's Note
desc: This time, we are looking for a kitten named Nargis with dark-gray fur. To call for Nargis's attention in cat language, you need to say "Meow! Meow meow, meow." Stress the first meow, and be quick while saying the following meows.

name: Sareh's Note
desc: This time, we are looking for a kitten named Rozan with gray and black stripes. To call for its attention in cat language, you should say "Meow meow meow, meow meow meow." Say it quickly with no elongation.

name: Fresh Nilotpala Lotus
desc: Flowers that grow in wetlands in the forest and bloom at night. Their fresh petals are important ingredients for the treatment of Eleazar.

name: Rose Sprout
desc: A flower sprouting in the faded Withering Zone, tender yet tough.

name: Eagle Feather of The Brave
desc: The brave young ones known as Javans are said to have this tough eagle feather as their symbol.

name: Florescent Talisman
desc: A talisman woven with childish skills. Its meaning remains unknown. The Dendro energy in it keeps the flower fresh for a long time. But apart from that, there is nothing special about this talisman.

name: Freshly-Picked Mushroom
desc: Mushrooms collected at the location designated by Hanbei. Although these mushrooms grow on tree trunks, they don't look special at all. They aren't going to cause any trouble, aren't they?

name: Strange Sumeru Rose
desc: A Sumeru Rose affected by the Ley Lines. It seems a little different from normal...

name: Riddle Note
desc:
"A mirror not made of glass reflects every drama."
Another riddle you got from the chest indicated by the previous riddle.
Who wrote these riddles...
Maybe the answer is hidden somewhere associated with dramas?

name: Riddle Note
desc:
"The sole path to knowledge."
A riddle that is surprisingly straightforward to read.
But what does "the sole path" mean in this case?

name: Riddle Note
desc:
"The flowers in the pond are blooming, with watery pearls there lingering."
The third riddle found from a chest.
Perhaps this might be some kind of plant?

name: Riddle Note
desc:
"Please go to the front door of the Temple of Knowledge at noon."
This riddle is like some kind of "invitation"...

name: Rafiq's Shipbuilding Materials
desc: Shipbuilding materials Rafiq bought. You've heard that these have cost him a fortune...

name: Little Dried Flower
desc: It looks like an ordinary little dried flower, but it was once a precious gift. It deserves to be cherished, just like the forgotten friendship of the past.

name: Activated·Canned Knowledge
desc: Canned Knowledge labeled "Swordfighting Techniques VIII." It was bought from Dori's booth at the price of 100,000 Mora at Paimon's instigation. You have no idea where the first seven in the series are, but things like "Combat Techniques" will always be useful. Well, probably.

name: Persikov's Manuscript
desc: Notes penned by the Fatui researcher Persikov. These notes contain a map, and if you follow its instructions, you should be able to find the crystalline cores that the Cognitive Mimicry device is missing...

name: Normal Wood
desc: Viktor bought this. He claims that he'll use it to do wood carving.

name: Fatui Meal
desc: A meal box containing two Panipuri. Viktor and Vsevolod should be a little hungry by now...

name: Treasure Map in a Box
desc: A treasure map placed at the bottom of a box. It indicates the location of the "good stuff" with simple markings.

name: Glinting Component
desc: A piece of the Primal Construct that barred your path. This component seems to be reacting with nearby devices, constantly gleaming and glinting as it does.

name: Sacred Seal: Valley
desc: A stone plate with ancient text on it that seems to have once been part of a certain building. The desert sands play host to many an unknown wish. Who made them, and who carries them now? Either way, researchers believe this symbol to have initially stood for "valley."

name: Sacred Seal: Bird Head
desc: A stone plate with ancient text on it that seems to have once been part of a certain building. The desert sands play host to many an unknown wish. Who made them, and who carries them now? Most believe the etchings here symbolize a bird's head.

name: Sacred Seal: Raised Arm
desc: A stone plate with ancient text on it that seems to have once been part of a certain building. The desert sands play host to many an unknown wish. Who made them, and who carries them now? Either way, researchers believe this symbol to have been a phonetic symbol, and that its extended meanings may have included respect or submission.

name: Sacred Seal: Sandstorm
desc: A stone plate with ancient text on it that seems to have once been part of a certain building. The desert sands play host to many an unknown wish. Who made them, and who carries them now? The shape of this symbol should be derived from the storms that ravage the desert.

name: Sacred Seal: Auricle
desc: A stone plate with ancient text on it that seems to have once been part of a certain building. The desert sands play host to many an unknown wish. Who made them, and who carries them now? The symbol on this plate looks like an auricle, but a consensus has not been reached on this matter.

name: Sacred Seal: Forest
desc: A stone plate with ancient text on it that seems to have once been part of a certain building. The desert sands play host to many an unknown wish. Who made them, and who carries them now? A majority of researchers believe this to represent the forest, and that this suggests that the modern-day desert was not always a desolate wasteland.

name: Sacred Seal: Thunderstrike
desc: A stone plate with ancient text on it that seems to have once been part of a certain building. The desert sands play host to many an unknown wish. Who made them, and who carries them now? The shape of this symbol should be derived from the lightning that is ever so rare a sight in the desert.

name: Sacred Seal: Danger
desc: A stone plate with ancient text on it that seems to have once been part of a certain building. The desert sands play host to many an unknown wish. Who made them, and who carries them now? The symbol seems to indicate the hazardous circumstance of hanging a chisel hammer on a cliff, and is thought to have emerged at a later date.

name: Sacred Seal: Chisel Hammer
desc: A stone plate with ancient text on it that seems to have once been part of a certain building. The desert sands play host to many an unknown wish. Who made them, and who carries them now? The symbol for a chisel hammer is one of the earliest words to emerge.

name: Sacred Seal: Sunrise
desc: A stone plate with ancient text on it that seems to have once been part of a certain building. The desert sands play host to many an unknown wish. Who made them, and who carries them now? The origin of this symbol is the rising sun.

name: Sacred Seal: Right to Rule
desc: A stone plate with ancient text on it that seems to have once been part of a certain building. The desert sands play host to many an unknown wish. Who made them, and who carries them now? This symbol is the spitting image of a ruler seated upon a throne.

name: Sacred Seal: Sheep Head
desc: A stone plate with ancient text on it that seems to have once been part of a certain building, though the origin of this writing seems unclear. The desert sands play host to many an unknown wish. Who made them, and who carries them now? Most believe that the etchings here symbolize a sheep's head.

name: Sacred Seal: Crocodile Head
desc: A stone plate with ancient text on it that seems to have once been part of a certain building. The desert sands play host to many an unknown wish. Who made them, and who carries them now? The source of this symbol is probably the Spinocrocodile's frighteningly huge maw.

name: Sacred Seal: Giant Serpent
desc: A stone plate with ancient text on it that seems to have once been part of a certain building. The desert sands play host to many an unknown wish. Who made them, and who carries them now? Though Haravatat researchers believe this to be a symbol for a giant serpent, Amurta researchers have proposed a different view, arguing that the Great Red Sand is not home to any snakes. As such, the meaning of and inspiration for this word is still being contested.

name: Sacred Seal: Ceremony
desc: A stone plate with ancient text on it that seems to have once been part of a certain building. The desert sands play host to many an unknown wish. Who made them, and who carries them now? The original meaning of this symbol was most likely "sacrifice," with an extended meaning of "rites" or "ceremonies" emerging later.

name: Sacred Seal: Labor
desc: A stone plate with ancient text on it that seems to have once been part of a certain building. The desert sands play host to many an unknown wish. Who made them, and who carries them now? The symbol here appeared at the same time as the chisel hammer, and is one of the earliest words to emerge.

name: Sacred Seal: Dune
desc: A stone plate with ancient text on it that seems to have once been part of a certain building. The desert sands play host to many an unknown wish. Who made them, and who carries them now? The civilization from the era of King Deshret had different words for dunes of different shapes, something that has brought researchers no lack of headaches.

name: Golden Rose Seeds
desc: Compared to Sumeru Roses, Golden Roses are a unique species more suited to the deserts. To survive, it has had to protect itself with a shield of mud and stone, but in the right environment, it may yet recoup its original beauty.

name: Transparent Ruins Record (I)
desc: A stone slate that you found in the transparent ruins near the Mausoleum of King Deshret. This seems to be a record left by a lost civilization.

name: Record of Lamb-Devourer Rock
desc: A stone slate that you found in the secret Eremite base within Lamb-Devourer Rock. This seems to be a record left by a lost civilization.

name: Record of the Tomb of Carouses
desc: A stone slate that you found in the Tomb of Carouses. This seems to be a record left by a lost civilization.

name: Soheil's Old Notes
desc: These are the notes left by Soheil, an Akademiya researcher, who entered the desert to study when he was young. They look very old, but they are not crinkled.

name: Record of Aaru's Shut
desc: A stone slate that you found at the highest point of the Mausoleum of King Deshret. This seems to be a record left by a lost civilization.

name: Twilight Theater Head's Notes
desc: The script for "Drama Phantasmagoria: Tale of the Sword-Wielding Princess!" The meandering scribbles appended to the script seem to be annotations from the theater troupe head, some of which contain such radical instructions as to render their adoption unlikely in the extreme.

name: Freshly-Picked Harra Fruit
desc: A freshly picked Harra Fruit. Perfect for cooking.

name: Unsigned Note
desc: An unsigned note. No one knows who left it...

name: Remelting Device
desc: This device, developed by alchemist Hajanad, is cleverly designed with an internal chamber capable of withstanding high pressure and high temperature to withstand the explosion from the "remelting effect". The special valve can be opened automatically at the right time to release the fully mixed medicament smoke and provide the user with assistance in combat. However, judging from some of its details, this experiment seems to be suffering from a shortage of funds. Hajanad's research doesn't seem to be all that well-funded...

name: Remelting Tablet
desc:
A masterpiece of the alchemist Hajanad, a truly special solid potion. Theoretically, this alchemy tablet can be stored for a long time and is quite safe and easy to carry and transport. However, when in use, the tablet needs to be put into the "remelting device," where the two solid agents will be mixed via micro-explosion to obtain complete efficacy.
And it is always a little disturbing to think that the device in hand may explode...

name: Pyro Shard
desc: A shard that broke off a larger Pyro Crystal. Gives 50 Pyro Energy when absorbed.

name: Hydro Shard
desc: A shard that broke off a larger Hydro Crystal. Gives 50 Hydro Energy when absorbed.

name: Dendro Shard
desc: A shard that broke off a larger Dendro Crystal. Gives 50 Dendro Energy when absorbed.

name: Electro Shard
desc: A shard that broke off a larger Electro Crystal. Gives 50 Electro Energy when absorbed.

name: Anemo Shard
desc: A shard that broke off a larger Anemo Crystal. Gives 50 Anemo Energy when absorbed.

name: Cryo Shard
desc: A shard that broke off a larger Cryo Crystal. Gives 50 Cryo Energy when absorbed.

name: Geo Shard
desc: A shard that broke off a larger Geo Crystal. Gives 50 Geo Energy when absorbed.

name: Primordial Elemental Shard
desc: A shard that broke off a larger Elemental Crystal. Gives 50 Elemental Energy when absorbed.

name: Pyro Jikaka
desc: A fruit taken from a Pyro Jikaka tree. Gives 30 Pyro Energy when eaten.

name: Hydro Jikaka
desc: A fruit taken from the Hydro Jikaka tree. Gives 30 Hydro Energy when eaten.

name: Dendro Jikaka
desc: A fruit taken from the Dendro Jikaka tree. Gives 30 Dendro Energy when eaten.

name: Electro Jikaka
desc: A fruit taken from the Electro Jikaka tree. Gives 30 Electro Energy when eaten.

name: Anemo Jikaka
desc: A fruit taken from the Anemo Jikaka tree. Gives 30 Anemo Energy when eaten.

name: Cryo Jikaka
desc: A fruit taken from the Cryo Jikaka tree. Gives 30 Cryo Energy when eaten.

name: Geo Jikaka
desc: A fruit taken from the Geo Jikaka tree. Gives 30 Geo Energy when eaten.

name: Standard Jikaka
desc: A fruit taken from a Standard Jikaka tree. Gives 30 Elemental Energy when eaten.

name: Wanderer's Advice
desc:
Character EXP material. Gives 1000 EXP.
These experiences are still beneficial even if one does not live in Teyvat.

name: Adventurer's Experience
desc:
Character EXP material. Gives 5000 EXP.
These experiences are very beneficial for journeys into the unknown.

name: Hero's Wit
desc:
Character EXP material. Gives 20000 EXP.
These experiences are extremely precious for a pilgrim traveling through Teyvat in order to be closer to Celestia.

name: Enhancement Ore
desc:
Weapon EXP material. Gives 400 EXP.
A refined ingot with endless possibilities that can be used to enhance weapons.

name: Fine Enhancement Ore
desc:
Weapon EXP material. Gives 2,000 EXP.
For reasons unknown, this special and refined ore can be absorbed by weapons to greatly increase their strengths.

name: Mystic Enhancement Ore
desc:
Weapon EXP material. Gives 10,000 EXP.
Legend has it that this refined ingot contains the memories of battles that had taken place in the land. The weapons that benefit from these memories naturally become sentient.

name: Brilliant Diamond Sliver
desc:
Character Ascension material.
"Welcome to this world."

name: Brilliant Diamond Fragment
desc:
Character Ascension material.
"Welcome to this world."

name: Brilliant Diamond Chunk
desc:
Character Ascension material.
"Welcome to this world."

name: Brilliant Diamond Gemstone
desc:
Character Ascension material.
"Welcome to this world."

name: Agnidus Agate Sliver
desc: Character Ascension Material.

name: Agnidus Agate Fragment
desc:
Character Ascension material.
"A pilgrimage for a wish; a battle to earn a name..."

name: Agnidus Agate Chunk
desc:
Character Ascension material.
"A pilgrimage for a wish; a battle to earn a name...
Burnt to cinders for a dream."

name: Agnidus Agate Gemstone
desc:
Character Ascension material.
"A pilgrimage for a wish; a battle to earn a name...
Burnt to cinders for a dream.
If the intention yet remains, achieved ██'s truth he has."

name: Varunada Lazurite Sliver
desc: Character Ascension Material.

name: Varunada Lazurite Fragment
desc:
Character Ascension material.
"My ideals have no stains."

name: Varunada Lazurite Chunk
desc:
Character Ascension material.
"My ideals have no stains.
I must correct you. People here bear no sins in the eyes of the gods..."

name: Varunada Lazurite Gemstone
desc:
Character Ascension material.
"My ideals have no stains.
I must correct you. People here bear no sins in the eyes of the gods... Only laws and the Tribunal can judge someone.
They can judge even me. So praise my magnificence and purity."

name: Nagadus Emerald Sliver
desc: Character Ascension Material.

name: Nagadus Emerald Fragment
desc:
Character Ascension material.
"I had a very, very long dream..."

name: Nagadus Emerald Chunk
desc:
Character Ascension material.
"I had a very, very long dream..."
"In it, people were holding hands, dancing in a circle, be they sages or fools, dancers or warriors, puppets or statues of gods..."

name: Nagadus Emerald Gemstone
desc:
Character Ascension material.
"I had a very, very long dream..."
"In it, people were holding hands, dancing in a circle, be they sages or fools, dancers or warriors, puppets or statues of gods..."
"That dancing circle embodied everything about the universe. Life has always been the end, while it is wisdom that shall be the means."

name: Vajrada Amethyst Sliver
desc: Character Ascension Material.

name: Vajrada Amethyst Fragment
desc:
Character Ascension material.
"This body is the noblest and most eminent of all in this world."

name: Vajrada Amethyst Chunk
desc:
Character Ascension material.
"This body is the noblest and most eminent of all in this world.
It should hold absolute control over this world."

name: Vajrada Amethyst Gemstone
desc:
Character Ascension material.
"This body is the noblest and most eminent of all in this world.
"It should hold absolute control over this world.
"It once promised its people a dream: the never-changing 'eternity.'"

name: Vayuda Turquoise Sliver
desc: Character Ascension Material.

name: Vayuda Turquoise Fragment
desc:
Character Ascension material.
"Still, the winds change direction."

name: Vayuda Turquoise Chunk
desc:
Character Ascension material.
"Still, the winds change direction.
Someday, they will blow towards a brighter future..."

name: Vayuda Turquoise Gemstone
desc:
Character Ascension material.
"Still, the winds change direction.
"Someday, they will blow towards a brighter future...
"Take my blessings and live leisurely from this day onward."

name: Shivada Jade Sliver
desc: Character Ascension Material.

name: Shivada Jade Fragment
desc:
Character Ascension material.
"Sorry..."

name: Shivada Jade Chunk
desc:
Character Ascension material.
"Sorry..."
"...to also have you shoulder the grievances of the world."

name: Shivada Jade Gemstone
desc:
Character Ascension material.
"Sorry... to also have you shoulder the grievances of the world.
"Since you could endure my bitter cold, you must have the desire to burn?
"Then, burn away the old world for me."

name: Prithiva Topaz Sliver
desc: Character Ascension Material.

name: Prithiva Topaz Fragment
desc:
Character Ascension material.
"The currencies that flow through this land are my flesh and blood."

name: Prithiva Topaz Chunk
desc:
Character Ascension material.
"The currencies that flow through this land are my flesh and blood.
For thus did I become the guarantor of the people's hard work, wisdom, and future."

name: Prithiva Topaz Gemstone
desc:
Character Ascension material.
"The currencies that flow through this land are my flesh and blood.
For thus did I become the guarantor of the people's hard work, wisdom, and future.
This is the trust I have placed in them. Betray it, and you taint my blood."

name: Dust of Azoth
desc:
A device that can transmute elemental Ascension Materials and change their Elemental Type.
Its practical uses notwithstanding, alchemy is the study of the nature of matter and the rules that underpin its transformations, and ultimately it seeks to comprehend the working principles of the world and the flow of the ley lines.
It is not known who would share alchemical achievements of this magnitude with the civilizations of the world and why. But although the power to fundamentally transmute elemental energy in its crystallized and inert form is a highly useful one, this device also conceals the grave danger of disrupting the elemental balance...

name: Teachings of Freedom
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Freedom is the spirit of the land of the wind.
The freedom to live is one of such. It is the freedom to live freely and healthily without concerns of one's own safety.

name: Guide to Freedom
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Freedom is the spirit of the land of the wind.
The freedom of travel is one of such. It is the freedom to traverse the land freely without being obstructed.

name: Philosophies of Freedom
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Freedom is the spirit of the land of the wind.
To sing is one such freedom. To sing on the land created by the Anemo Archon is to send your heart away with the song on the wind.

name: Teachings of Resistance
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Resistance is the backbone of the land of the wind.
The history of Mondstadt is one of resistances. People rose up to prevent past conflicts from ever being forgotten, like sprouts breaking through the soil, like the eternal wind eroding through stone walls.

name: Guide to Resistance
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Resistance is the backbone of the city of Wind.
The history of Mondstadt is one of resistances. People rose up to grant the citizens of Mondstadt the freedom they now enjoy, like the Anemo Archon blowing away the snow, or like Vennessa rising up to fight.

name: Philosophies of Resistance
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Resistance is the backbone of the land of the wind.
The history of Mondstadt is one of resistances. People rose up to allow the future Mondstadt's poetry to freely be that of the wind and be spread across the land.

name: Teachings of Ballad
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Poetry is the soul of the land of the wind.
Poetry is the manifestations of beautiful feelings. On a beautiful day, the breezes carry with them poetry that touches the heart of people like the wind caressing the leaves.

name: Guide to Ballad
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Poetry is the soul of the land of the wind.
Poetry is the manifestations of the will to encourage. In the dark days, the gales in the streets and alleyways whisper words of fury, like the battle drums, like the low rumbling before the storm.

name: Philosophies of Ballad
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Poetry is the soul of the land of the wind.
Poetry is the manifestations of the desire to spread the word. Though nothing is eternal, though nothing will be the same, the wind's poetry will still spread beyond the skies, the land, the seas to every corner of the world.

name: Teachings of Prosperity
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Prosperity is the people's pursuit in the land of Geo.
Prosperity is the blessing of Liyue, it is the foundation of the great city built by the gods and the people of Liyue, and it is the source of the peace and safety of the land.

name: Guide to Prosperity
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Prosperity is the people's pursuit in the land of Geo.
Prosperity is the promise made by Liyue to its children: To repay the hard-working laborers with enough gold to brighten up this land.

name: Philosophies of Prosperity
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Prosperity is the people's pursuit in the land of Geo.
Prosperity is Liyue's past, present, and future. This prosperity is unmatched and unobtainable by any other nations — it all belongs to Liyue and its inhabitants.

name: Teachings of Diligence
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Industriousness is the foundation of the land of Geo.
Diligence is having the bravery and the strength to conquer mountains and seas and to pursue gold and prosperity through honest, hard work.

name: Guide to Diligence
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Industriousness is the foundation of the land of Geo.
Industriousness is the catalyst that flows in the blood of the people of Liyue, able to turn rocks into gold. It is what lies behind the greatness of its great commercial port.

name: Philosophies of Diligence
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Industriousness is the foundation of the land of Geo.
Industriousness is believing in one's own ability to earn a place in the land of the gods through sweat, wisdom, and power.

name: Teachings of Gold
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Gold is the symbol of the land of Geo.
Gold is the blood that flows deep within Liyue's veins, the muscle that makes up Liyue's beating heart, and the bones that make Liyue stand proud.

name: Guide to Gold
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Gold is the symbol of the land of Geo.
Gold symbolizes conversion. This is the unspoken understanding between Liyue's mountains, land, city, and people. In Liyue, industriousness is converted into gold, and gold into prosperity.

name: Philosophies of Gold
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Gold is the symbol of the land of Geo.
Gold is the wealth of Liyue, but Liyue's true wealth is the hearts of its people that shine like gold.

name: Crown of Insight
desc:
A precious Talent Level-Up material.
Once a medium for the storage and transfer of wisdom in ancient times. Now, wisdom is found in ancient texts and in profound speech. Nevertheless, this Crown of Insight must still be able to impart some transcendent power and wisdom to its bearer.

name: Teachings of Transience
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Transience is the dream of the nation of thunder.
Fleeting glories are the highest expression of mortal beauty, for are we mortals not like the flashing lightning itself? Like a lovely dream or blossoming spark, we shall leave a gorgeous mark on the eternal night sky.

name: Guide to Transience
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Transience is the dream of the nation of thunder.
We find the greatest joys in mortal life in transient dreams, for is life itself not like the shadow of the thunder? Pursue your dreams into the clouds if you wish, and enjoy the unexpected silence of the dim lamp-lit nights.

name: Philosophies of Transience
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Transience is the dream of the nation of thunder.
The fleeting nature of this mortal world is the essence of beauty, for are our lives in this world not akin to the levin flash? Yet the might of the divine comes suddenly, and before the roar of eternity, who can stand?

name: Teachings of Elegance
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Elegance is the form of the nation of thunder.
Elegance brooks no flattery, and the elegant are ever noble. They are like the sea eagles who soar on high to contend with the resounding storms. They will not cater to philistine vulgarity, as one would not cast a flower crown into the mud, staining its dignity.

name: Guide to Elegance
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Elegance is the form of the nation of thunder.
Elegance shuns arrogance. The elegant are ever humble, and only by discarding vanity and sloth may one see clearly — and is there not beauty and loveliness even in the basest of appearances?

name: Philosophies of Elegance
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Elegance is the form of the nation of thunder.
Elegance abhors vulgarity, and the elegant ever walk alone. Resisting base evils, unmoved by base loves, never taking refuge in base ignorance — that is how one perceives the chasm between the elegant and the contemptuous.

name: Teachings of Light
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Light is the yearning of the land of thunder.
The ruler who claims to have perceived all forever aims to hoard celestial glory. But this vision that cannot be shared only leads people to long for it more fiercely, like moths diving into the flame.

name: Guide to Light
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Light is the yearning of the land of thunder.
Though the sun rays themselves should be blocked by layers upon layers of clouds, there are still those in the thunder god's land who dream of piercing that wrathful sea of lightning to pursue the glory of the divine, fearing not that they shall be cruelly struck down.

name: Philosophies of Light
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Light is the yearning of the land of thunder.
Though they must live forever on the earth, humanity will always reach for the light. Mortals will pursue and surpass, and they will never stop. A sealed eternity may, perhaps, look magnificent, but its essence is death.

name: Teachings of Admonition
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Admonition is the branches of the nation of wisdom.
Admonition comes from a pure heart. Only sensible words of goodwill can express profound wisdom and free the sprout of knowledge from the shackles of arrogance.

name: Guide to Admonition
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Admonition is the branches of the nation of wisdom.
Admonition is paired with wise thinking. Careful deliberation affords humble words a clarity that convinces the wise and enlightens the foolish. Such words allow wisdom to flow like an unobstructed river.

name: Philosophies of Admonition
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Admonition is the branches of the nation of wisdom.
Admonition is completed by good deeds. What is done confers real meaning upon what is said. When one's mind, words, and deeds are aligned, their nourishment shall guarantee the fruition of wisdom's tree.

name: Teachings of Ingenuity
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Ingenuity is the leaf-veins of the nation of wisdom.
Ingenuity springs forth from benevolent consideration. They say that "a poisonous tree bears no kind fruit." Similarly, ingenious nascent ideas are always born from determined and benign minds, for only they are worthy bearers of wisdom.

name: Guide to Ingenuity
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Ingenuity is the leaf-veins of the nation of wisdom. Ingenuity sets words of integrity on the right path. One who thinks out of goodwill and in a clever and careful fashion never deviates from the path of boons. Yet one who thinks with contempt and malice shall taint their words with despicable colors.

name: Philosophies of Ingenuity
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Ingenuity is the leaf-veins of the nation of wisdom.
Ingenuity is completed by harmonious conduct. What is done completes what is thought. Wisdom blooms where the mind, words, and practice converge.

name: Teachings of Praxis
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Praxes are the roots of the nation of wisdom.
Praxes stem from an unwavering will. All wisdom is manifested through the unyielding pursuit of goodness. Where goodness is not practiced, ingenuity and eloquence wither.

name: Guide to Praxis
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Praxes are the roots of the nation of wisdom.
Praxes validate words of honesty. Though one speaks and acts out of goodwill, one has not yet obtained wisdom. Wisdom, born from action, is a signet pressed upon honest words.

name: Philosophies of Praxis
desc:
Talent Level-Up material.
Praxes are the roots of the nation of wisdom.
Praxes bring forth the fruit of wisdom. Practice grants itself meaning, and it is only by treading a path that unites action, speech, and thought that the wise may reach perfection.

name: Sanctifying Unction
desc:
Artifact EXP material. Gives 2,500 EXP.
Material that contains the distilled essence of great power. It can contribute to the enhancement of artifacts.

name: Sanctifying Essence
desc:
Artifact EXP material. Gives 10,000 EXP.
Artifacts are themselves the physical manifestation of ideals and memories. Materials such as this, which contain the distilled essence of the power thereof, can make these memories and ideals clearer and stronger still.

name: Test Stamina Growth Item
desc: Test item for increasing stamina

name: Test Temporary stamina Growth Item
desc: Test item for increasing max stamina temporarily

name: Anemoculus
desc: A substance that has accumulated intense Anemo energy. Offer it to the Statue and help reinstate the power it has lost over the years.

name: Elemental Dust
desc: Shattered fragments of the Oculus Crystal. Shows hidden treasure nearby.

name: Geoculus
desc: A substance that has accumulated intense Geo energy. Offer it to the Statue and help reinstate the power it has lost over the years.

name: Adventure Treasure Pack
desc: Daily highscore reward. Grants 1 random T1 Character Ascension material.

name: Skyrider Greatsword Chest
desc: This chest opens automatically, granting a Skyrider Greatsword.

name: Mondstadt Shrine of Depths Key
desc:
A key that can break the seal on the ancient Shrines of Depths scattered around Mondstadt.
These Shrines of Depths sealed themselves off when the civilization that built them was lost. Keys lost deep within domains are able to break the seals. Or perhaps that, for a moment, these keys help the seals to forget all that they have lost.

name: Liyue Shrine of Depths Key
desc:
A key that can break the seal on the ancient Shrines of Depths scattered around Liyue.
These Shrines of Depths sealed themselves off when the civilization that built them was lost. Keys lost deep within domains are able to break the seals. Or perhaps that, for a moment, these keys help the seals to forget all that they have lost.

name: Inazuma Shrine of Depths Key
desc:
A key that can break the seal on the ancient Shrines of Depths scattered around Inazuma.
These Shrines of Depths sealed themselves off when the civilization that built them was lost. Keys lost deep within domains are able to break the seals. Or perhaps that, for a moment, these keys help the seals to forget all that they have lost.

name: Fragile Resin
desc:
An item used to restore Original Resin by 60 points.
This crystalline substance pulsates with a little energy that can be absorbed by Original Resin.
The flow of energies of all sorts is the source of many wonders and challenges in this world. Those same energies are also contained within this crystal.

name: Crimson Agate
desc: A type of crystal formed from the combination of concentrated life force with an energy unique to Dragonspine. Makes for an ideal nutrient for growing Frostbearing Trees.

name: Crimson Agate (Display)
desc: A type of crystal formed from the combination of concentrated life force with an energy unique to Dragonspine. Makes for an ideal nutrient for growing Frostbearing Trees.

name: Transient Resin
desc:
An item that can be used to replenish Original Resin. Once used, it will replenish 60 Original Resin.
Once obtained, it will automatically dissipate after a period of time.
·The expiration time will be calculated from the Monday after this item is obtained, and it will disappear seven days from then.
·Multiple Transient Resins obtained on different weeks will have their expiration dates counted independently.

Pure energy that will dissipate with time. In this, it is similar to all else that is lovely in this world. But seize this opportunity and go make the world a slightly better place, as is fitting for one who dwells within the bounds of "time."

name: Vial of Adeptal Speed
desc: A small bottle that seals some adeptal energy within. Will immediately complete a furnishing when used.

name: Electroculus
desc: A substance that has accumulated intense Electro energy. Offer it to the Statue and help reinstate the power it has lost over the years.

name: Moonchase Charm
desc: These jade talismans have been placed in various areas by the Adventurers' Guild. They are made from crystal-clear and gently lustrous Plaustrite Shards. It is said that these talismans contain the essence of the bright white moon and store the reminiscences that people have of festivals past.

name: Lumenspar
desc:
A sky-blue crystal that glitters so brightly that it brings forth echoes of the heavens above, which cannot be seen from underground...
If you hold it up to your ear, you can almost hear a soft sigh coming from within.
This might sound strange, but this crystal also gives off a faint warmth.

name: Dendroculus
desc: A substance that has accumulated intense Dendro energy. Offer it to the Statue and help reinstate the power it has lost over the years.

name: Sumeru Shrine of Depths Key
desc:
A key that can break the seal on the ancient Shrines of Depths scattered around Sumeru.
These Shrines of Depths sealed themselves off when the civilization that built them was lost. Keys lost deep within domains are able to break the seals. Or perhaps that, for a moment, these keys help the seals to forget all that they have lost.

name: Dish
desc: Items created by cooking

name: Suspicious Fisherman's Toast
desc: Onion-covered toast. Not quite cooked right. You'll notice its imperfection, even if you eat it while fishing.

name: Fisherman's Toast
desc: Onion-covered toast. A favorite amongst fishermen, they will stuff a bag with it and sit by the river all day.

name: Delicious Fisherman's Toast
desc: Onion-covered toast. Exudes a wonderful aroma. Are the fish biting for the bait, or is it the toast they're after?

name: Suspicious Teyvat Fried Egg
desc: An egg fried on one side. A bit hard in the middle. One can only hope it still has its nutrients.

name: Teyvat Fried Egg
desc: An egg fried on one side. The yolk flows out nicely when broken. So satisfying.

name: Delicious Teyvat Fried Egg
desc: An egg fried on one side. With a taste of the summer sun, it invigorates you from the first bite.

name: Suspicious Steak
desc: A grilled steak. Its color is a little bleak, almost as if it feels sorry for itself for being a sorry excuse for a steak.

name: Steak
desc: A grilled steak. High heat has locked the juices in, giving one high expectations for when the meat is cut open.

name: Delicious Steak
desc: A grilled steak. Juicy, flavorsome, fragrant steak. One bite and you feel yourself come alive.

name: Outrider's Champion Steak!
desc: Amber's specialty. One side is obviously uncooked. The other side gives off a subtle scent of something burnt. Close your eyes and have a big mouthful, just to keep Amber happy if nothing else.

name: Suspicious Chicken-Mushroom Skewer
desc: A skewer of mushrooms and poultry. At first glance it's hard to tell which is which.

name: Chicken-Mushroom Skewer
desc: A skewer of mushrooms and poultry. Fresh poultry is complimented by fragrant mushrooms. Don't be picky, chow down!

name: Delicious Chicken-Mushroom Skewer
desc: A skewer of mushrooms and poultry. All the best the wild has to offer are pierced on just one stick.

name: Fruity Skewers
desc: Kaeya's specialty. A chewy skewer with a rich sweet aftertaste. Wait... Is this really the smell of fruit?

name: Suspicious Flaming Red Bolognese
desc: Bolognese covered with a meat sauce. A bit chewy and annoyingly sticks to your teeth.

name: Flaming Red Bolognese
desc: Bolognese covered with a meat sauce. The meaty, herby aroma really gets your appetite going.

name: Delicious Flaming Red Bolognese
desc: Bolognese covered with a meat sauce. The beautiful, authentic flavors take you on a culinary adventure from the first bite to the last.

name: Mysterious Bolognese
desc: Lisa's specialty. With an inexplicable aura, this bolognese is so exotic that you can never have enough. Did she actually enchant it with some kind of magic?

name: Suspicious Radish Veggie Soup
desc: Radish-based vegetable soup. The vegetables within appear to have been victims of a frost.

name: Radish Veggie Soup
desc: Radish-based vegetable soup. Its flavor is delicately between tart and sweet. With luscious radish, it's a well-balanced dish.

name: Delicious Radish Veggie Soup
desc: Radish-based vegetable soup. The clear aromas are perfectly accompanied by a sunny summer afternoon.

name: Suspicious Tea Break Pancake
desc: A stack of round pancakes. A burnt scent masks what you can only assume should be a sweet taste. The berries are the only thing saving this dish.

name: Tea Break Pancake
desc: A stack of round pancakes. A staple originating from afternoon tea in manors. Only the best berries should be picked for this dish.

name: Delicious Tea Break Pancake
desc: A stack of round pancakes. Tender and fluffy, the sweet-smelling pancakes taste like clouds. A heavenly delicacy, no doubt.

name: Suspicious Fried Radish Balls
desc: Fried Radish Balls. Way too oily, and leaves you looking for something to drink to cut through the grease.

name: Fried Radish Balls
desc: Fried Radish Balls. Fragrant and crispy. Make sure to eat them while they're hot! Said to be a recipe from Liyue.

name: Delicious Fried Radish Balls
desc: Fried Radish Balls. It's insane that something so delicious comes from plain old radishes! All who eat them will truly understand Liyue's culinary reputation.

name: Suspicious Satisfying Salad
desc: A vegetable salad. Regrettably, it seems the best time to plate the potatoes and boiled eggs was missed.

name: Satisfying Salad
desc: A vegetable salad. Not just steamed potatoes and fresh vegetables, but also a hard-boiled egg to top it off. Satisfying to both the eyes and stomach.

name: Delicious Satisfying Salad
desc: A vegetable salad. Fresh, light, and varied. You'd never get tired of eating this, even if you had to eat it for the rest of your life.

name: Suspicious Sweet Madame
desc: Honey-roasted fowl. The sweet flowers have been burnt off, revealing the bitter taste of the overcooked fowl.

name: Sweet Madame
desc: Honey-roasted fowl. The honey and sweet flowers come together to complement the tender fowl meat.

name: Delicious Sweet Madame
desc: Honey-roasted fowl. Tender and sweet, the meat has perfectly fused with the honey, ensuring the only thing left of this dish will be the cleanly-picked bones.

name: Suspicious Northern Smoked Chicken
desc: Smoked fowl paired with vegetables. It's true. You really ought to try your own cooking before serving it to your guests. It's not too late to make a new one, perhaps?

name: Northern Smoked Chicken
desc: Smoked fowl paired with vegetables. A staple for Northerners, often made for honored guests.

name: Delicious Northern Smoked Chicken
desc: Smoked fowl paired with vegetables. A dish fit for a king. Go on, find one and serve him with pride.

name: Suspicious Cream Stew
desc: A meat and vegetable stew. Surprisingly dry for something that's meant to have liquid.

name: Cream Stew
desc: A meat and vegetable stew. The thick juices taste great with the tender meat and vegetables.

name: Delicious Cream Stew
desc: A meat and vegetable stew. These warm, buttery ingredients are so good that you almost want to dive into the cream stew and cuddle up with them.

name: Spicy Stew
desc: Barbara's specialty. Carrots cut into cute little stars make this dish... Wait, AHH, where did this spiciness come from!?

name: Suspicious Mushroom Pizza
desc: A pizza covered in cheese and mushrooms. If you can bite through the brick-like texture... At least it can ease your hunger.

name: Mushroom Pizza
desc: A pizza covered in cheese and mushrooms. When still warm, the cheese becomes stretchy and gooey, making it extremely satisfying to eat.

name: Delicious Mushroom Pizza
desc: A pizza covered in cheese and mushrooms. It's a party in your mouth and the cheese and mushrooms invited all their delicious friends.

name: Invigorating Pizza
desc: Jean's specialty. This pizza almost seems more art than food. Just one slice is enough to have you raring to go. Is this what keeps Jean working so hard?

name: Suspicious Mondstadt Hash Brown
desc: A fried cake of mashed potatoes. It's said that a hash brown without jam is not worthy of the Mondstadt name... But is this even a hash brown?

name: Mondstadt Hash Brown
desc: A fried cake of mashed potatoes. A little bit of pinecone helps give it a nice crunch, and great with a bit of jam. Loved by people of all ages.

name: Delicious Mondstadt Hash Brown
desc: A fried cake of mashed potatoes. Close your eyes and feel the mild breeze and sweet dew that Mondstadt offers.

name: Puppy-Paw Hash Brown
desc: Razor's specialty. Carefully shaped to resemble a wolf's paw. You can really feel the effort he has put into trying human cooking.

name: Suspicious Calla Lily Seafood Soup
desc: A balanced combination of seafood. The bitterness of the calla lily, the astringency of the mint, the fishiness of the crab... Getting all the negatives together like this takes skill.

name: Calla Lily Seafood Soup
desc: A balanced combination of seafood. The delicacy of crab and mint make for a clear soup, and the calla lily brings it a refreshing taste.

name: Delicious Calla Lily Seafood Soup
desc: A balanced combination of seafood. The crab, mint, and Calla Lily come together perfectly to dance on your tongue. It reminds you of playing barefoot by the lake in summer.

name: Suspicious Sautéed Matsutake
desc: Sautéed slices of Matsutake. A shame that control of the fire was lost. Best you can do now is try to trick people who didn't see you cooking it into thinking they are just potato chips.

name: Sautéed Matsutake
desc: Sautéed slices of Matsutake. Cooked in butter, it's crisp outside yet tender inside. Eat it before someone steals it from you.

name: Delicious Sautéed Matsutake
desc: Sautéed slices of Matsutake. So smooth and fragrant, eating them is like having the bursting vitality of spring absorbed into your stomach.

name: Suspicious "Pile 'Em Up"
desc: A rich, meaty dish. The meat must have been stacked wrong... Yeah, that's it. Now, can this actually be served...?

name: "Pile 'Em Up"
desc: A rich, meaty dish. Originally a Mondstadt dish made of steaks, potatoes and cheese, it has since become synonymous with Ludi Harpastum.

name: Delicious "Pile 'Em Up"
desc: A rich, meaty dish. Piled in just the right way to be both aesthetically pleasing and delicious all the way through. I wonder if we can pile it a little higher...

name: "Once Upon a Time in Mondstadt"
desc: Diluc's specialty. Feast your eyes and then your stomach upon this delicacy as the soft ribs melt in your mouth. Who knew Diluc was able to cook this well?

name: Suspicious Cold Cut Platter
desc: A plate of cold cut meat. Seems a little too cold, probably not good for those with bad teeth or sensitive stomachs.

name: Cold Cut Platter
desc: A plate of cold cut meat. An equal balance of bacon, ham and sausage keeps everyone happy.

name: Delicious Cold Cut Platter
desc: A plate of cold cut meat. The seasoning is just delightful enough to bring out the flavors perfectly. With a mouth full of meaty ecstasy, one worries about nothing.

name: Suspicious Sticky Honey Roast
desc: A meat dish in a sweet honey sauce. The sauce has stuck like glue to the meat, forming a homogeneous mass that tastes neither of honey nor meat.

name: Sticky Honey Roast
desc: A meat dish in a sweet honey sauce. The carrots take the gamey edge off the meat, and the sauce brings it all together sweetly. The perfect warm dish for a cold winter night.

name: Delicious Sticky Honey Roast
desc: A meat dish in a sweet honey sauce. The warm honey draws out the flavor of the meat, creating a flavor explosion akin to bathing in the warm summer sun.

name: Suspicious Crab, Ham & Veggie Bake
desc: A somewhat luxurious bake. By looking at it, no one can tell what it is made of... or what it lacks.

name: Crab, Ham & Veggie Bake
desc: A luxurious bake. Cracks through the golden outer skin reveal a medley of rosy ham and bright vegetables. How tantalizing!

name: Delicious Crab, Ham & Veggie Bake
desc: A luxurious bake. The scent is so rich and heavenly. You'll only be done once you've licked the plate clean.

name: Suspicious Jade Parcels
desc: An exquisite-looking dish. Food ingredients of different degrees of doneness are wrapped in shriveled vegetables. It looks depressing to say the least.

name: Jade Parcels
desc: An exquisite-looking dish. The ham's sweetness is locked inside the fresh vegetables, drizzled with a spicy broth. Delicious is an understatement.

name: Delicious Jade Parcels
desc: An exquisite-looking dish. The sweetness of the ham and the crisp lotus seeds are a match made in heaven. The aromatic broth pours down like the dawning light, caressing your tongue with an unworldly delicious taste.

name: Suspicious Zhongyuan Chop Suey
desc: A seasoned and cooked meat dish. Even if the dish was extremely delicious, it surely doesn't look the part. Even the most popular stalls would have trouble selling this.

name: Zhongyuan Chop Suey
desc: A seasoned and cooked meat dish. Though it contains animal organ meat and bits and scraps of other things, the strong-flavored seasonings have masked the stench of the meat. Many have had this dish for the entirety of their lives without knowing "chop suey" is not actually a swear word in the local language.

name: Delicious Zhongyuan Chop Suey
desc: A seasoned and cooked meat dish. The authentic "Liyue taste" of this aromatic dish makes it a comfort food for golden-agers that may bring a tear to their eyes.

name: Suspicious Black-Back Perch Stew
desc: A poached fish dish. It has essentially lost all the taste of the fish itself to the spicy taste of the chili peppers. Only a selected few enjoy such a sensory overload on their tongues.

name: Black-Back Perch Stew
desc: A poached fish dish. The fresh and tasty fish fillets are tender and juicy. The secret to this recipe is adding powdered Violetgrass into the heated oil to give the dish that aromatic scent. It's spicy, but not too spicy.

name: Delicious Black-Back Perch Stew
desc: A poached fish dish. The fish fillets are so tender and juicy that they almost seem to come alive in your mouth. The sense of loss is so unbearable that when you swallow a piece down, you just have to treat yourself to another.

name: Suspicious Squirrel Fish
desc: A hard-to-prepare fish dish. Sure, you can make out the shape of the fish, but you can't see how it's related to any squirrel. It just proves that the more complicated the dish is to prepare, the harder it is to prepare it well.

name: Squirrel Fish
desc: A hard-to-prepare fish dish. The fish is first completely deboned before crisscross cuts are made on the skin. The fish is then coated in flour and deep-fried to a golden-brown color, then served with ketchup drizzled on top. It is tender and juicy on the inside and crispy on the outside. The dish resembles a squirrel's tail to a certain degree, hence the name.

name: Delicious Squirrel Fish
desc: A hard-to-prepare fish dish. The fish is expertly handled to exhibit an elegant shape; however, the exquisitely balanced sweet-and-sour taste is really where the dish truly comes alive. The culinary skills involved in preparing this dish can impress even the greatest chefs of Liyue.

name: Suspicious Almond Tofu
desc: A dessert made from ground almonds. The almond milk is chilled without being properly ground and strained. You can only lie to yourself that its rough texture is what makes it special.

name: Almond Tofu
desc: A dessert made out of almond. It has a silky-smooth texture with a long-lasting aroma of almond. It's named tofu only because of its tofu-like shape.

name: Delicious Almond Tofu
desc: A dessert made from ground almonds. It has the exquisite look and texture of a piece of white jade, and could pass as an art piece — so much so that you could not entertain the idea of actually eating it.

name: Suspicious Jueyun Chili Chicken
desc: Chicken in a dressing, served cold. The chicken probably isn't properly marinated, so it's only salty on the outside but bland on the inside. The taste reminds you of water-poached chicken breasts.

name: Jueyun Chili Chicken
desc: Chicken in a dressing, served cold. The way the dish has been prepared captures the succulence of the chicken perfectly. Beneath the glowing gold skin, the meat has a mildly hot flavor.

name: Delicious Jueyun Chili Chicken
desc: Chicken in a dressing, served cold. The chicken is extremely tender, juicy, and sweet. The delicious taste transports you to the realm of dreams.

name: Suspicious Jewelry Soup
desc: A simple vegetable soup. The bland soup and dull vegetables remind you of the dying vegetables on abandoned and barren farmlands.

name: Jewelry Soup
desc: A simple vegetable soup. Snapdragon, tofu, and lotus seeds are put into boiling water and simmered. Jewelry Soup earned its luxurious name from the look of the ingredients used, but contrary to its name, the soup is commonly prepared and served in ordinary households.

name: Delicious Jewelry Soup
desc: A simple vegetable soup. The mild-tasting soup is filled with the fragrance of fresh vegetables. This down-to-earth and heart-warming soup can rival any luxurious dish.

name: Suspicious Matsutake Meat Rolls
desc: A pan-fried meat dish. Though the dry and tough texture is miles away from what it could be, the Matsutake is too nutritious to let it go to waste.

name: Matsutake Meat Rolls
desc: A pan-fried meat dish. Ground meat is put on the Matsutake and gently pan-fried on low heat so the Matsutake can fully take in the aromatic juice of the meat. It's a mouthwatering delicacy in all of its glory.

name: Delicious Matsutake Meat Rolls
desc: A pan-fried meat dish. It combines the essences of the mountains and the nourishments of the celestial bodies. It is a very nutritious dish that will surely bring a smile to your face.

name: Suspicious Mora Meat
desc: A large hunk of minced meat packaged inside a pastry. The tough pastry shell almost seems to sally out against your teeth as you bite into it. If you fight through the greasiness and only chew on the minced meat, you can sort of taste its flavor.

name: Mora Meat
desc: A large hunk of minced meat packaged inside a pastry. When you split the pastry in two, minced meat spills out. The taste of meat grease is all but gone, and the baking process has brought out the sweetness of the pastry. Such pastries are usually stamped with the word "Mora," all the better to represent wealth and fortune.

name: Delicious Mora Meat
desc: A large hunk of minced meat packaged inside a pastry. With a crispy crust and tender meat, this legendary delicacy is so succulent that not even Mora laid in front of you could distract you from enjoying it.

name: Suspicious Mondstadt Grilled Fish
desc: Fish grilled thoroughly with moderate fire. Sadly, it's a bit too well done. The charred smell and the dry texture are not too impressive.

name: Mondstadt Grilled Fish
desc: Fish grilled thoroughly with moderate fire, making it completely dry and crispy. The sprinkled pepper on top brings out the freshness of the fish.

name: Delicious Mondstadt Grilled Fish
desc: Fish grilled thoroughly with moderate fire, locking the delicious juice inside the meat under the crispy skin. A small bite is all that's needed to unlock its wondrous and delicious taste.

name: Suspicious Stir-Fried Filet
desc: Slices of meat stir-fried on high heat — but for so long that they are now indistinguishable from the accompanying Jueyun Chili. Best served with rice, if served at all.

name: Stir-Fried Filet
desc: Sliced meat flash-fried in a wok. The mild Jueyun Chili adds just the right amount of kick to the delicious aroma of the meat. Perfect as an appetizer and also goes well with rice.

name: Delicious Stir-Fried Filet
desc: Slices of meat stir-fried on high heat. The spiciness is as a blaze amidst a field of snow that ignites your appetite and leaves you craving more.

name: Suspicious Golden Crab
desc: A crab dish cooked in the ancient ways. The flour granules within have congealed like gravel, and have some crab shell mixed in. But compared to the blandness of the crab meat, the taste of crab shell is at least worth having a go at.

name: Golden Crab
desc: A crab dish cooked in the ancient ways. The crab has been chopped into pieces and battered with flour, before being stir-fried till golden and rich with flavor. It is worthy of the word "gold," whether in terms of appearance or quality.

name: Delicious Golden Crab
desc: A crab dish cooked in the ancient ways. The aroma of the crab meat inundates the room the instant it leaves the frying pan, and a single bite fills one's palate with the countless rustic flavors of a fishing village hometown. It seems that such simple yet timeless village customs held the secret to this lavish, golden sumptuousness all along.

name: Suspicious Crystal Shrimp
desc: One of Liyue's traditional snacks. The dull outer skin has a rather sticky mouthfeel which, when combined with the dry stuffing within, makes this dish a torment best ended sooner.

name: Crystal Shrimp
desc: One of Liyue's traditional snacks. The stuffing is taken from whole fresh shrimp, and the glistening quality of the flour can be guessed at from the translucence of the outer skin. Has a springy, tasty chew.

name: Delicious Crystal Shrimp
desc: One of Liyue's traditional snacks. The outer skin is as clear its crystal namesake, and when it enters the mouth, one's tongue could be forgiven for thinking that the fresh shrimp within is still alive. Those who eat it can only lament that four pieces per serving is far, far too few.

name: Suspicious Grilled Tiger Fish
desc: A fish kebab grilled over an open flame. You can barely see that this charred lump is indeed grilled fish, and upon further investigation, the fish scales mixed in confirm that this is indeed the case.

name: Grilled Tiger Fish
desc: A fish kebab grilled over an open flame. The fish is a fresh catch straight from the harbor, lightly seasoned and swiftly grilled. Its aroma attracts the street cats. Indeed, freshness is the secret of flavor.

name: Delicious Grilled Tiger Fish
desc: A fish kebab grilled over an open flame. The shimmering golden skin has locked the fresh and tender meat in. You cannot help but sigh in satisfaction as you chew on it. Not a scrap of meat here will go uneaten, not even those stuck firmly to the bamboo stick.

name: Suspicious Barbatos Ratatouille
desc: A simple chowder with a long history. Thought the Anemo Archon is said to symbolize freedom, perhaps this dish has been a bit too liberal in the making. Perhaps the name Stormy Stew might be more fitting here.

name: Barbatos Ratatouille
desc: A simple chowder with a long history. The ingredients are similarly traditional and simple. No matter where you are, a piping-hot chowder of this sort can always give you a sense of real and unsurpassed satisfaction.

name: Delicious Barbatos Ratatouille
desc: A simple chowder with a long history. After much careful stewing, the flavors of three different vegetables have been blended to perfection. Like this, it is not hard to imagine why someone once called it "the best chowder I've ever tasted."

name: A Buoyant Breeze
desc: Venti's specialty. Other than the Cecilia flowers used for decoration, the ingredients are no different from normal. But if you taste it carefully, you can taste the flavor of "a wind that brings hope and tiny twists of fate." Perhaps... this is exactly what he wants.

name: Der Weisheit Letzter Schluss (Life)
desc: Mona's specialty. A great work from a great astrologer. Its greatest aspect lies with its cost-effectiveness in filling one's stomach.

name: Fish-Flavored Toast
desc: Klee's specialty. By way of apology for wantonly using her bombs to scare away the fish, Jean instructed Klee to make this toast for the fishermen. It's filling and tasty. Klee will never starve again, even after a whole day of blast fishing.

name: Teyvat Charred Egg
desc: Bennett's specialty. For some reason, every single fried egg is a little burnt around the edges. That said, the burnt crisp does lends a whole new flavor to the dish.

name: Die Heilige Sinfonie
desc: Fischl's specialty. The exquisite presentation doth seem to communicate some incomprehensible enigma. When partaking, if one were to gaze upon Fischl, one might see her expectant gaze peek through the gaps of her fingers, which she is using to cover half her face... Is this also part of the mystery?

name: Lighter-Than-Air Pancake
desc: Noelle's specialty. These thick pastries are the special afternoon snacks of the Knights of Favonius. They give people the sense that they have fallen upon a layer of fluffy clouds, and seeing Noelle's smile makes the feeling all the sweeter!

name: Suspicious Lotus Seed and Bird Egg Soup
desc: A steamed egg dish. The lengthy steaming process has caused unusual honeycomb figure to appear on the surface of the egg custard. It goes without saying that there isn't hardly a hint of bitterness left in the lotus.

name: Lotus Seed and Bird Egg Soup
desc: A steamed egg dish. The clear, gold colors of the egg custard have been embellished with several lotus roots. Regardless of whether it is breakfast or a post-meal snack, its superior nutritional value can greatly nourish the body.

name: Delicious Lotus Seed and Bird Egg Soup
desc: A steamed egg dish. The succulent eggs melt right in your mouth, and before you know it, a smooth and subtle sweetness of newly sprung lotus flowers covers your tastebuds.

name: Suspicious Adeptus' Temptation
desc: A complex, famous type of Liyue cuisine. Without having mastered the art of simmering, the resulting stew-like dish has a salty, fishy taste. But, just considering the costly ingredients will be enough to keep you going until the pot's empty.

name: Adeptus' Temptation
desc: A complex, famous type of Liyue cuisine, in which specially selected ingredients are submerged and slowly boiled in soup stock. The recipe scribbled from memory alone was enough to urge the adepti to once again return to the world of men.

name: Delicious Adeptus' Temptation
desc: A complex, famous type of Liyue cuisine. This dish is a rare and exquisite mix of both land and sea, combining countless delicious delicacies in one flavor-filled pot. Each mouthful is a moment to remember — it's even irresistible enough to entice the adepti down from their celestial abode.

name: Suspicious Golden Shrimp Balls
desc: A deep-fried shrimp dish. Hastily cast into hot oil and promptly forgotten about, the result is a disastrous combination of raw shrimp and burnt potato strips.

name: Golden Shrimp Balls
desc: A deep-fried shrimp dish. The aroma assaults your senses, while the crispy potatoes bring out the light sweetness of the shrimp meat. This, in tandem with its cute, small shape, makes it very enticing indeed.

name: Delicious Golden Shrimp Balls
desc: A deep-fried shrimp dish. From the rich, indulgent scent of crispy golden potato strips, to the satisfying crunch as you take your first bite, to the grand finale of delicious sweet shrimp, this dish is pure pleasure.

name: Suspicious Qingce Stir Fry
desc: A dish cooked over a roaring fire. This one was a failed test run, being unpleasantly bitter and uncomfortably spicy. You could try mixing it with rice — or you could simply discard it and eat the rice instead.

name: Qingce Stir Fry
desc: A dish cooked over a roaring fire. They say it was originally just a rustic dish that everyone in Qingce Village knew how to make. But quite unexpectedly, its crispy and spicy dishes gained the recognition of people from elsewhere, and thus began to spread throughout the Liyue region.

name: Delicious Qingce Stir Fry
